obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (63962)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=63962&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Inland Vessels Act, 2021.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line
  line `Official Gazette, appoint:`
  line
  line `Provided that different dates may be appointed for bringing into force different provisions of this Act`
  line `in different States or Union territories, as it may deem fit by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 16th February, 2022,--,Section 1 and 106, vide Notification S.O. 743(E), dated 16th February, 2022, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
  line
  line `7th of June, 2022,--Section 2 to 105 and 107 to 114, vide Notification S.O. 2604(E), dated 7th June, 2022, see Gazette of`
  line `India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (63963)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Application and scope.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=63963&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise expressly provided in this Act, the provisions of`
  line `Chapters I, III, X, XVI and XVIII shall apply to all inland vessels plying within inland waters of India,`
  line and--
  line
  line `(a) Chapters IV, V, VI, VIII, IX, X, XI, XII, XIII and XIV shall apply to all mechanically`
  line `propelled vessels registered under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) Chapters VIII, IX, X, XI, XII and XIII shall apply to vessels registered under such laws in`
  line `force in India other than this Act, or registered in such laws in force in any country other than India;`
  line `but endorsed or recognised under this Act for the purpose of plying within inland waterways;`
  line
  line `(c) Chapters IV, V, VI, VII, VIII, IX, X, XI, XII, XIII and XIV shall apply to all vessels`
  line `identified as special category vessels plying or using inland waterways;`
  line
  line `(d) Chapter XVII shall apply to all non-mechanically propelled inland vessels.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the Central Government or the State`
  line `Government, as the case may be, may extend the application of any Chapter or provision of this Act to`
  line `any class or category of inland vessels, or to any region of inland waters, by notification in the Official`
  line Gazette.
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (63964)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=63964&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,---`
  line
  line `(a) "authorised insurer" means any insurance company carrying on any class of marine insurance`
  line `business, which is registered or recognised by the Central Government under any law for the time`
  line `being in force in India;`
  line
  line `(b) "bareboat charter" means an arrangement for the hiring of a vessel without crew, where the`
  line `charterer is responsible for appointing the crew and making other arrangements;`
  line
  line `(c) "bareboat charter-cum-demise" is a bareboat charter where the ownership of the vessel is`
  line `intended to be transferred after a specified period to the company to which it has been chartered;`
  line
  line `(d) "cargo terminal" means a place designated for the loading, or unloading, or any other allied`
  line `processes of such loading or unloading of cargo in a port, jetty, wharf or such other places developed`
  line `within inland waters for the purpose of loading and unloading of cargo;`
  line
  line `(e) "casualty" includes any vessel which---`
  line
  line `(i) is lost, abandoned, materially damaged;`
  line
  line `(ii) causes loss of material or damage to any other vessel;`
  line
  line `(iii) causes any loss of life or personal injury;`
  line
  line `(iv) causes pollution as a result of or in connection with its operation;`
  line
  line `(f) "central database"means the centralised record maintained for recording the data and details`
  line of---
  line
  line `(i) vessels;`
  line
  line `(ii) registration of vessels;`
  line
  line `(iii) crew and manning in the vessels;`
  line
  line `(iv) certificates issued in respect of vessels;`
  line
  line `(v) reception facilities; and`
  line
  line `(vi) such other data,`
  line
  line `to be recorded and maintained in the form of an electronic portal or in such other form and manner as may`
  line `be prescribed by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(g) "certificate of insurance" means a certificate issued by an authorised insurer in pursuance of`
  line `the insurance premium paid by the insured, and includes a cover note complying with such`
  line `requirements as may be prescribed by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(h) "competent authority" means the authority referred to in section 6;`
  line
  line `(i) "court" means any civil court, revenue court or High Court having jurisdiction over the matters`
  line `of liabilities and offences as provided in this Act including investigation and inquiry into claims`
  line `arising out of causalities and accidents within its jurisdiction;`
  line
  line `(j) "cover note" includes any note of undertaking issued by the insurer who promises to cover the`
  line `liability and to indemnify the losses incurred by the insured as provided in the contract of insurance;`
  line
  line `(k) "crew" means personnel employed for operation or serving on an inland vessel other than`
  line `master or passengers as a part of performing the functions of manning;`
  line
  line `(l) "dangerous cargo" means any cargo, which, due to its nature, form or content as a whole or in`
  line `part, are declared as dangerous or potentially dangerous while carried in on any class or category of`
  line `inland vessels in inland waters under this Act or any other law for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(m) "dangerous goods" means any goods, which, due to its nature, form or content as a whole or`
  line `in part, are declared as dangerous or potentially dangerous while carried in on any class or category of`
  line `inland vessels in inland waters under this Act or any other law for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(n) "designated authority" means the authorities appointed by State Government under subsection (3) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(o) "fishing vessel" means a vessel fitted with mechanical mode of propulsion, which is`
  line `exclusively engaged in fishing for profit, within inland waters;`
  line
  line `(p) "hazardous chemical" means any chemical, which has been designated as pollutants under this`
  line `Act or any other law for the time being in force in India;`
  line
  line `(q) "inland vessel" includes any mechanically propelled inland vessel or non-mechanically`
  line `propelled inland vessel which is registered and plying in inland waters, but does not include---`
  line
  line `(i) a fishing vessel registered under the Merchant Shipping Act, 1958 (44 of 1958) or the`
  line `Marine Products Export Development Authority Act, 1972 (13 of 1972); and`
  line
  line `(ii) any vessel that are specified as not to be inland vessels by notification by the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this clause, it is clarified that a vessel registered under the`
  line `Merchant Shipping Act, 1958 (44 of 1958) and plying within the inland waters shall be deemed to be`
  line `an inland vessel registered under this Act;`
  line
  line `(r) "inland waters", for the purpose of inland navigation, includes any---`
  line
  line `(i) canal, river, lake or other navigable water inward of baseline or as may be declared by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(ii) tidal water limit, as may be declared by notification in the Official Gazette by the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(iii) national waterways declared by the Central Government; and`
  line
  line `(iv) other waters as may be declared by notification in the Official Gazette by the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(s) "lien" is a legal right or interest that a creditor has in the inland vessel or any property thereof,`
  line `retained until a debt or duty is secured, or the performance of some other obligation is satisfied;`
  line
  line `(t) "limitation of liability" means the rate or extent of liability within which the owner or such`
  line `other persons entitled under this Act, may limit the liability or be permitted to limit or cap the liability`
  line `arising out of claims, in accordance with the procedure laid down and the rates, as may be specified in`
  line `this Act or as may be prescribed by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(u) "load line" means a water line which is marked on an inland vessel to denote the safe carrying`
  line `or loading capacity of such vessel;`
  line
  line `(v) "master" includes any person including serang or such other person, who is in command or in`
  line `charge of any inland vessel, and does not include a pilot or harbour master;`
  line
  line `(w) "material fact" means a fact of such a nature, which determines the judgment of a prudent`
  line `insurer, in assessing the extent of his liability, premium to be charged, conditions to be specified and`
  line `such other terms to be entered and incorporated in a policy of insurance governing the relationship`
  line `with the insured;`
  line
  line `(x) "material particular" means any particular of such a nature, which determines the judgment of`
  line `a prudent insurer, in assessing the extent of his liability, premium to be charged, conditions to be`
  line `specified and such other terms to be entered and incorporated in a policy of insurance governing the`
  line `relationship with the insured;`
  line
  line `(y) "mechanically propelled inland vessel" means---`
  line
  line `(i) any inland vessel in the inland waters which is propelled by mechanical means of`
  line `propulsion; or`
  line
  line `(ii) floating units, floating surfaces, dumb vessels, barges, rigs, jetties or such other nonmechanically propelled inland vessel, which are towed or pushed with the assistance of another`
  line `mechanically propelled vessel and used for carriage, storage, transportation and accommodation`
  line `of passengers and cargo in or through inland waters;`
  line
  line `(z) "minimum manning requirement" means the standard and number of persons required for safe`
  line `manning and navigation of vessels, as may be prescribed by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(za) "non-mechanically propelled inland vessel" means any vessel which is not a mechanically`
  line `propelled inland vessel;`
  line
  line `(zb) "notification" means a notification published in the Gazette of India or the Official Gazette`
  line `of a State, as the case may be, and the expression notify with its grammatical variation and cognate`
  line `expressions shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(zc) "obnoxious substance" means any substance, which has been designated as pollutants under`
  line `this Act or any other law for the time being in force in India;`
  line
  line `(zd) "official number" means the number assigned to any vessel by the Registrar of Inland`
  line `Vessels or such other person appointed under this Act, to be affixed or displayed on a conspicuous`
  line `part of such vessel to refer, distinguish and identify one vessel from another;`
  line
  line `(ze) "oil" means any edible oil carried on vessel as cargo or persistent oil such as crude oil, heavy`
  line `diesel oil, lubricating oil and white oil, carried on board of a vessel as cargo or fuel;`
  line
  line `(zf) "oily mixture" means a mixture with any oil content;`
  line
  line `(zg) "owner" means operator, charterer, beneficial owner or registered owner, who is responsible`
  line `for the activities of the vessel and shall be under obligation to comply with the provisions of this Act`
  line `in relation to, or in possessing express or implied title under this Act or any other law for the time`
  line `being in force;`
  line
  line `(zh) "passenger" means any person carried on board of a vessel, except persons employed or`
  line `engaged in any capacity on board of the vessel in connection with the business of the vessel;`
  line
  line `(zi) "passenger terminal" means the terminal designated for the embarking or dis-embarking of`
  line `passengers and the permitted cargo, in a port, jetty, wharf or like places;`
  line `(zj) "passenger vessel" means any vessel permitted to carry more than twelve passengers;`
  line
  line `(zk) "pilot" means a person appointed by the owner of the vessel to assist the master or to steer`
  line `the vessel in such area of inland water in accordance with the mandatory requirements, as specified`
  line `in section 83;`
  line
  line `(zl) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules by the Central Government or a State Government, as`
  line `the case may be;`
  line
  line `(zm) "priority of lien"means the ranking of liens in the order in which they are perfected or`
  line `recorded in the book of registry maintained at every port or place of registry;`
  line
  line `(zn) "reciprocating country" means any country, as may on the basis of reciprocity, specified by`
  line `notification by the Central Government to be a reciprocating country for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(zo) "recognised organisation" means any organisation recognised and authorised by the Central`
  line `Government to perform and execute the functions involved in survey, classification or certification of`
  line vessels;
  line
  line `(zp) "salvage" means an act of the salvor in retrieving or saving any property or life in danger due`
  line `to wreck or accident and includes all expenses incurred by the salvor in the performance of salvage`
  line services;
  line
  line `(zq) "salvor" means any person who conducts salvage operations;`
  line
  line `(zr) "service provider" includes any person, who in the capacity of owner or operator of an inland`
  line `vessel used or plying in inland waters, providing services to any service user for the purposes of`
  line `transportation, storage or accommodation;`
  line
  line `(zs) "service user" includes any person who as a passenger or owner of cargo or freight`
  line `forwarder, uses the services of any inland vessel in the inland waters for transportation, storage or`
  line `accommodation purposes;`
  line
  line `(zt) "special category vessel" means a mechanically propelled inland vessel that is identified`
  line `under this Act as special by considering its use, purpose, function or utility or the means of`
  line `propulsion including the fuelling system or source of power for propulsion, such as liquefied natural gas, electrical propulsion, the design, dimensions of construction or areas of operation or such other`
  line `criteria or standards;`
  line
  line `(zu) "vessel" includes every description of water craft used or capable of being used in inland`
  line `waters, including any ship, boat, sailing vessel, tug, barge or other description of vessel including`
  line `non-displacement craft, amphibious craft, wing-in-ground craft, ferry, roll on-roll-off vessel,`
  line `container vessel, tanker vessel, gas carrier or floating unit or dumb vessel used for transportation,`
  line `storage or accommodation within or through inland waters;`
  line
  line `(zv) "wreck" means a state of any vessel, or goods or a part or property of such vessel or carried`
  line `on the vessel,---`
  line
  line `(i) which have been cast into or have fallen into the inland waters and then sunk and remain`
  line `under water or remains floating on the surface; or`
  line
  line `(ii) which have sunk in the inland waters, but are attached to a floating object in order that`
  line `they may be found again; or`
  line
  line `(iii) which are intentionally thrown away or abandoned without hope or intention of recovery;`
  line or
  line
  line `(iv) which by its presence in inland waters, is a hazard or causes impediment to navigation, or`
  line `adversely affects safety of life or causes pollution.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (63965)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Declaration of inland water area into Zones.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=63965&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, for the purposes`
  line `of this Act, declare by notification any inland water area to be a “Zone” depending on the maximum`
  line `significant wave height criteria specified in sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of sub-section (1), the State Government may classify the maximum significant`
  line `wave height criteria into the following Zones, namely:—`
  line
  line `(i) Zone 1 refers to the area (other than Zone 2 or Zone 3) where the maximum significant wave`
  line `height does not exceed 2.0 metres;`
  line
  line `(ii) Zone 2 refers to the area (other than Zone 3) where the maximum significant wave height`
  line `does not exceed 1.2 metres; and`
  line
  line `(iii) Zone 3 refers to the area where the maximum significant wave height does not exceed 0.6`
  line metres.
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (63966)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Administrative role of Central Government and State Governments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=63966&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central`
  line `Government may, by general or special order, direct that any power, authority or jurisdiction exercisable`
  line `by it under, or in relation to any such provision of this Act, or the rules made thereunder, or as may be`
  line `specified in the order allocating the duties, shall, subject to such conditions and restrictions as may be so`
  line `specified, also be exercisable by the competent authority or by such other officer as may be specified in`
  line `that order.`
  line
  line `(2) On and from the date of issue of notifications or rules made by the Central Government under the`
  line `provisions of this Act, the provisions shall,—`
  line
  line `(a) uniformly apply in whole or in any part of India, as may be specified therein; and`
  line
  line `(b) prevail over such notifications or rules, as the case may be, issued or made by the State`
  line Governments.
  line
  line `(3) The State Governments may, by notification, appoint one or more designated authorities within`
  line `their respective jurisdiction for the purposes of exercising or discharging the powers, authority or duties`
  line `conferred, by or under this Act and the rules made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) and section 6, the existing administrative`
  line `authorities constituted under State Governments or Union territory Administrations may continue to be`
  line `the designated authorities for the purposes of sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(5) The State Government may, for the purposes of implementing the various provisions of this Act`
  line `and the rules made thereunder, by general or special order, direct that any power or authority conferred`
  line `under this Act, subject to such conditions and restrictions as it may think fit, be exercised or discharged`
  line `by the respective designated authorities or any officer or any other organisation or body.`
  line
  line `(6) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, the State Government shall have the power to make rules`
  line `and shall exercise the powers conferred on it, as provided by or under this Act.`
  line
  line `(7) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary in this Act, for the purposes of administration of the`
  line `non-mechanically propelled inland vessels, as specified in Chapter XVII, the Central Government shall`
  line `have no powers of administration and shall only provide assistance to the respective State Government,`
  line `on receipt of official request from such State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (63967)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Competent authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=63967&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The Inland Waterways Authority of India, constituted under section 3 of`
  line `the Inland Waterways Authority of India Act, 1985 (82 of 1985) shall be the competent authority for the`
  line `purpose of exercising or discharging the powers, authority or duties conferred, by or under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (63968)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Power to classify and categorise for purpose of survey.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=63968&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of this`
  line `Chapter, ---`
  line
  line `(a) the classification of mechanically propelled vessels;`
  line
  line `(b) the criteria for such classification; and`
  line
  line `(c) the standards of design, construction, fitness and crew accommodation of such vessels,`
  line
  line `shall be such, as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government shall classify and categorise mechanically propelled inland vessels on the`
  line `basis of criteria and standards referred to in sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (63969)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Construction, alteration or modification of mechanically propelled inland vessel.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=63969&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) No`
  line `person shall construct any mechanically propelled inland vessel, or alter or modify any mechanically`
  line `propelled inland vessel so as to affect its strength, stability or safety, except with prior approval of the`
  line `designated authority, in such manner as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The list of alterations or modifications referred to in sub-section (1), which would affect the`
  line `strength, stability or safety of any mechanically propelled inland vessel, and the criteria therefor, shall be`
  line `such as may be specified by the Central Government, by notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (63970)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Survey of vessels.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=63970&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The standard for type and periodicity of surveys for every mechanically`
  line `propelled inland vessel shall be such as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The owner, operator, master or construction yard or any other applicant, as the case may be, shall`
  line `submit a request for survey in such form and content as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (63971)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Appointment and qualifications of surveyors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=63971&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of this Act, the State Government`
  line `may, by notification, appoint officers or persons as surveyors of inland vessels and such surveyors shall be`
  line `deemed to be public servants within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
  line
  line `(2) The minimum criteria and qualifications for the appointment of surveyors, which the State`
  line `Governments shall adopt in the appointment of surveyors, shall be such as may be prescribed by the`
  line `Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (63972)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Powers of surveyors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=63972&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) On receipt of the application from the owner or master or construction`
  line `yard for conducting survey, in such form and within such time as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line `Government, the surveyor may board or enter and inspect a mechanically propelled inland vessel:`
  line
  line `Provided that the surveyor shall not unnecessarily hinder the loading or unloading of cargo or;`
  line `embarking or dis-embarking of passengers of the mechanically propelled inland vessel, or unnecessarily`
  line `detain or delay her from proceeding on any voyage.`
  line
  line `(2) The owner, operator, master and crew of the mechanically propelled inland vessel shall render the`
  line `surveyor, all reasonable facilities for conducting survey, and all information with respect to such`
  line `mechanically propelled inland vessel, and her machinery or any part thereof, and all equipment and`
  line `articles on board, as he may require for the purposes of a survey.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (63973)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Grant of certificate of survey and procedures.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=63973&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) On completion of survey of a mechanically`
  line `propelled inland vessel, the surveyor shall forthwith issue the applicant, a declaration of survey, valid for`
  line `such period and in such form, as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government shall, if satisfied that all the provisions of this Act have been complied`
  line `with in respect of a declaration submitted under sub-section (1), and on receipt of payment of fee, as may`
  line `be prescribed by the State Government, issue a certificate of survey to the applicant.`
  line
  line `(3) A certificate of survey granted under this section shall be in such form as may be prescribed by`
  line `the Central Government, and shall contain a statement to the effect that all the provisions of this Act with`
  line `respect to the survey of the mechanically propelled inland vessel and the declaration of surveyor have`
  line `been complied with, and shall set forth such particulars or such other terms and conditions, as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) The State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, delegate all or any of the`
  line `functions assigned to it by the Central Government under this section:`
  line
  line `Provided that no delegation shall be made to authorise the grant of a certificate of survey by the`
  line `surveyor, who made the declaration of survey under sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (63974)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Provisional certificate of survey and its effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=63974&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) On receipt of application and the fee from`
  line `the owner or operator of any mechanically propelled inland vessel, the surveyor who conducted the`
  line `survey, may grant a provisional certificate of survey extending the validity of the prevailing certificate of survey`
  line `by endorsement, in such form and for such period, as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Any mechanically propelled inland vessel, which has been issued with a provisional certificate of`
  line `survey or endorsement under sub-section (1), may proceed on voyage or use in service, temporarily,`
  line `pending the issue of the certificate of survey, in such manner and subject to the conditions as may be`
  line `prescribed by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (64075)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Mechanically propelled inland vessels not to proceed without certificate of survey, and requirement of Zone to be specified in such certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64075&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) No mechanically propelled inland vessel`
  line `shall be used nor proceed on voyage, without a valid certificate of survey that shall provide or indicate`
  line `among others, the Zone intended for operation or applicable voyage or service of such vessel.`
  line
  line `(2) The certificate of survey shall have effect throughout India, unless otherwise specified therein and`
  line `subject to such other conditions as may be specified by the competent authority.`
  line
  line `(3) The certificate of survey shall be valid for such period as may be specified by notification by the`
  line `Central Government and shall not be in force--`
  line
  line `(a) after the expiration of the period specified in the certificate of survey; or`
  line
  line `(b) after notice has been issued to cancel or suspend such certificate.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing in this section shall prevent the State Government from excluding a mechanically`
  line `propelled inland vessel from the requirement under sub-section (1), on an application made by the owner`
  line `or master of the vessel for permission to proceed on a voyage; during the interval between the date on`
  line `which the certificate of survey expires and the earliest possible date of renewal.`
  line
  line `(5) After cessation of a certificate of survey, a valid certificate of survey shall be obtained only after a`
  line `fresh survey of the mechanically propelled inland vessel has been conducted by any surveyor appointed`
  line `under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (63976)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Suspension and cancellation of certificate of survey.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=63976&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may suspend`
  line `or cancel a certificate of survey, if it has reason to believe that—.`
  line
  line `(a) the declaration of the surveyor of the sufficiency and good condition of the hull, engines or`
  line `other machinery or of any of the equipment of the mechanically propelled vessel has been`
  line `fraudulently or erroneously made; or.`
  line
  line `(b) the certificate has otherwise been granted upon false or erroneous information; or.`
  line
  line `(c) since the making of the declaration, the hull, engine or other machinery, or any of the`
  line `equipment of the mechanically propelled vessel have sustained any material damage, or have`
  line `otherwise become insufficient..`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government shall issue the notice of suspension of certificate of survey to the owner,`
  line `operator, master or construction yard by stating the errors to be rectified and conditions that have to be`
  line `complied with by the owner, operator, master or construction yard within three months from the date of`
  line `issuance of such notice, in such manner as may be prescribed by that Government..`
  line
  line `(3) In the event of non-compliance of the notice of suspension by the owner, operator, master or`
  line `construction yard within the period specified therein, the State Government shall record such noncompliance and shall issue the notice of cancellation of certificate of survey, which shall come into force`
  line `with immediate effect.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (63977)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Delivery of expired, suspended or cancelled certificate of survey.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=63977&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The owner or master`
  line `shall deliver the certificate of survey, which has expired or has been suspended or cancelled, to such`
  line `officer as the State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government shall record the details of the cancelled certificate in the book of registry`
  line `maintained by the Registrar of Inland Vessels.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (64076)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title Registration.
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64076&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any mechanically propelled inland vessel, which is wholly owned by---`
  line
  line `(a) a citizen of India; or`
  line
  line `(b) a co-operative society registered or deemed to be registered under the Co-operative Societies`
  line `Act, 1912 (2 of 1912); or`
  line
  line `(c) a body established under any Act relating to co-operative societies for the time being in force`
  line `in any State; or`
  line
  line `(d) a company registered under the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013); or`
  line
  line `(e) a partnership firm registered under the Limited Liability Partnership Act, 2008 (6 of 2009); or`
  line
  line `(f) any other body including a partnership firm, trust or societies established by or under any`
  line `Central or State enactment and which has its principal place of business in India;`
  line
  line `(g) any legal business combination, otherwise allowed under the existing commercial law for the`
  line `time being in force in India, within the permissible foreign direct investment limits in the sector and`
  line `having its principal place of business in India,`
  line
  line `shall be registered under the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) A foreign vessel, other than vessels registered or obligated to register under the Merchant`
  line `Shipping Act, 1958 (44 of 1958), chartered on bareboat charter-cum-demise by an Indian charterer, for`
  line `the purposes of plying exclusively within inland waters, shall be registered under the provisions of this`
  line Chapter.
  line
  line `(3) The inland vessels registered under this Act may also be registered under the Merchant Shipping`
  line `Act, 1958 (44 of 1958).`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of sub-section (2), "Indian charterer" shall mean a person referred to`
  line `in clauses (a) to (g) of sub-section (1), who has chartered a vessel on bareboat charter-cum-demise`
  line contract.
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (64077)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Requirement of certificate of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64077&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) A mechanically propelled inland vessel required to be`
  line `registered under this Chapter, shall not proceed on any voyage or be used for any service, unless it has a valid`
  line `certificate of registration granted under this Act in respect thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the authority appointed or authorised under this`
  line `Chapter may—`
  line
  line `(a) permit any mechanically propelled inland vessel, built at any place other than a port or place`
  line `of registry, to make her first voyage through the inland waters to any such port or place for the`
  line `purpose of registration; or`
  line
  line `(b) permit the vessel registered under any law for the time being in force in India for which`
  line `provisions have been made under this Act to conduct voyage within the inland waters; or`
  line
  line `(c) permit any mechanically propelled vessel registered under such laws of countries other than`
  line `India, which shall only be permitted to ply within the inland waters subject to compliance of such terms and`
  line `conditions as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (63979)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Owner or master to carry certificate of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=63979&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The owner or master of an inland`
  line `vessel shall carry a valid certificate of registration issued under this Chapter and shall make available for`
  line `inspection, when demanded by the officers appointed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government or such other officer appointed or authorised under this Chapter may detain`
  line `any mechanically propelled inland vessel required to be registered under this Act, until the respective`
  line `owner, operator or master of such vessel furnishes a valid certificate of registration.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (63980)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Appointment of ports or places of registry and Registrars of Inland Vessels.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=63980&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the`
  line `purposes of this Chapter, the State Government may, by notification, —`
  line
  line `(a) appoint ports or places of registry; and`
  line
  line `(b) appoint Registrar of Inland Vessels at the said ports or places of registry, who shall be deemed`
  line `to be a public servant within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
  line
  line `(2) A Registrar of Inland Vessels shall, in respect to the port or place of registry for which he is`
  line `appointed, perform his functions as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (63981)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Book of registry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=63981&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Registrar of Inland Vessels shall maintain and keep a book of`
  line `registry, which shall have record of all particulars contained in the form of certificate of registration as`
  line `may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Registrar of Inland Vessels shall report the details of the book of registry or entries made`
  line `therein, to the State Government at regular intervals, in such manner and period as may be prescribed by`
  line `the State Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Government shall report and update the Central Government in respect of—`
  line
  line `(a) the designated ports and places of registry;`
  line
  line `(b) the details of officers appointed or authorised under this Chapter; and`
  line
  line `(c) the details of registrations as entered in the book of registry,`
  line
  line `to facilitate and administer the registration processes under this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (63982)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Central database of inland vessels.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=63982&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall appoint officers to maintain`
  line `a central data base for inland vessels, in such form and manner, and the functions of the officers so`
  line `appointed shall be such, as may be prescribed by that Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (63983)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Application and processes of registration of vessels.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=63983&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) The owner or master, may make an`
  line `application for registration of a mechanically propelled inland vessel, which has a valid certificate of`
  line `survey issued under this Act, in such form, manner and along with such particulars, as may be prescribed`
  line `by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The list of documents to be submitted or adduced by the applicants for registration, in addition to`
  line `the particulars referred to in sub-section (1), shall be such as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(3) Every application for registration shall be made to the Registrar of Inland Vessels, within the`
  line `jurisdiction of the respective State in which the owner of the mechanically propelled inland vessel—`
  line
  line `(a) ordinarily resides; or`
  line
  line `(b) has the principal place of business or the officially registered office.`
  line
  line `(4) If the Registrar of Inland Vessels is satisfied that the vessel or the application submitted for`
  line `registration is not in compliance with the provisions of this Act, he may refuse to register a mechanically`
  line `propelled inland vessel for reasons to be recorded in writing and shall provide the applicant a note`
  line `containing the reasons for such refusal.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (63984)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Grant of certificate of registration and marking of vessel.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=63984&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of`
  line `section 23, the Registrar of Inland Vessels shall, grant the certificate of registration to the applicant, who`
  line `has paid such fee, as may be prescribed by the State Government, and assign the official number to such`
  line `registered vessel.`
  line
  line `(2) The certificate of registration shall be in such form and content, as may be prescribed by the`
  line `Central Government, and shall contain the following particulars, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) registered address of the owner and other ownership details;`
  line
  line `(b) details of mortgage, if any;`
  line
  line `(c) official number;`
  line
  line `(d) classification and category of vessel;`
  line
  line `(e) any other particular, as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The owner shall display the official number on a conspicuous part of the vessel, as may be`
  line `prescribed by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (63985)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Effect of certificate of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=63985&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) The certificate of registration granted under section 24`
  line `shall be deemed to be valid in all States and Union territories, unless otherwise specified therein.`
  line
  line `(2) The certificate of registration issued under this Chapter shall be conclusive proof of ownership`
  line `and title, as declared by the applicant and as entered in the book of registry by the Registrar of Inland`
  line Vessels.
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, any person who has beneficial interest of`
  line `ownership in the mechanically propelled inland vessel or shares therein, shall have the same rights as that`
  line `of the registered owner and shall be deemed as owner of such vessel for the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (63986)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Duplicate certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=63986&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the certificate of registration issued under this Chapter is lost or`
  line `destroyed, the registered owner shall apply for a duplicate certificate to the Registrar of Inland Vessels,`
  line `who has issued such certificate of registration, in such form and manner as may be prescribed by the State`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(2) The Registrar of Inland Vessels shall, on receipt of application under sub-section (1) and such fees`
  line `or additional fees, as may be prescribed by the State Government, issue the duplicate certificate of`
  line registration.
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (63987)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Provisional certificate of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=63987&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Registrar of Inland Vessels may, pending`
  line `issuance of the certificate of registration, upon an application and on payment of fee, by the applicant,`
  line 15
  line `issue a provisional certificate of registration valid for such period as may be prescribed under sub-section`
  line `(2).`
  line
  line `(2) The application, fee and the issuance of provisional certificate of registration referred to in subsection (1) shall be in such form, rate and manner, as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) During the period of validity of the provisional certificate of registration, the owner, operator,`
  line `master or construction yard shall implement and comply with all necessary steps to be taken to have the`
  line `vessel registered under this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (63988)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Registration of modifications or alterations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=63988&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) The owner, operator or master of any`
  line `mechanically propelled inland vessel, shall make an application, in such form, manner and within such`
  line `period as may be prescribed by the State Government, to effect any alteration or modification affecting`
  line `the strength, stability or safety of such mechanically propelled inland vessel along with the respective`
  line `certificate of survey, in which such alteration or modification have been approved, to the respective`
  line `Registrar of Inland Vessels, who has issued the certificate of registration.`
  line
  line `(2) The Registrar of Inland Vessels shall, on receipt of application and the certificate of survey and on`
  line `receipt of such fee, as may be prescribed by the State Government, either cause the alteration or`
  line `modification to be registered and entered in the certificate of registration, or direct that the vessel be`
  line `registered anew:`
  line
  line `Provided that, where the Registrar of Inland Vessels, directs that the vessel be registered anew, he`
  line `shall grant a provisional certificate for a specific period describing the vessel as altered or endorse on the`
  line `existing certificate about the particulars of the alteration.`
  line
  line `(3) Any mechanically propelled inland vessel found plying without complying with sub-section (1) or`
  line `sub-section (2) shall be detained by such authority or officer as the State Government may, by general or`
  line `special order, appoint in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (63989)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Change of residence or place of business.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=63989&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the owner of a mechanically propelled inland`
  line `vessel ceases to reside or carry on business at the registered address recorded in the certificate of`
  line `registration of the vessel, such person shall comply with the procedures prescribed under sub-section (2)`
  line `by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of sub-section (1), the procedures to be complied with by the owner of any`
  line `mechanically propelled inland vessel, who ceases to be the owner or applies for the requirement of`
  line `transfer of registry or any such circumstances leading to change of the registered address, shall be such as`
  line `may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (63990)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Prohibition against transfer of ownership of registered vessel.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=63990&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `No mechanically propelled`
  line `inland vessel registered with the registering authority of a State Government under this Chapter, shall be`
  line `transferred to a person residing in any country other than India, without the prior approval of the Registrar`
  line `of Inland Vessels, who has originally granted the certificate of registration and such a transfer shall be`
  line `validated only if made in compliance with such procedures as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (63991)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Suspension of certificate of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=63991&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Registrar of Inland Vessels may at any time,`
  line `require any mechanically propelled inland vessel within the local limits of his jurisdiction to be inspected`
  line `by such authority as the State Government may, by general or special order, appoint in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) As a result of such inspection, if the Registrar of Inland Vessels has reason to believe that after the`
  line `granting of the certificate of registration, the mechanically propelled inland vessel became unfit to ply in`
  line `inland waters, order suspension of the certificate of registration of the said vessel for such period as he`
  line `may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(3) The Registrar of Inland Vessels shall, before suspending a certificate of registration, provide to the`
  line `owner, operator or master an opportunity of being heard, and record the reasons for such suspension.`
  line
  line `(4) The Registrar of Inland Vessels who suspends the certificate of registration under sub-section (2),`
  line `shall issue a notice of suspension to the registered owner stating the reasons for suspension and the conditions to be complied within such period, as may be prescribed by the State Government, for`
  line `withdrawal of such order of suspension.`
  line
  line `(5) Where the registration of a mechanically propelled inland vessel is suspended under sub-section`
  line `(2) by any Registrar of Inland Vessels, other than the Registrar of Inland Vessels who has originally`
  line `issued the certificate of registration, the former shall intimate the latter, regarding such order of`
  line `suspension or withdrawal of such order of suspension; and the latter shall enter such order in the book of`
  line `registry in which the registration of the vessel is originally recorded.`
  line
  line `(6) The Registrar of Inland Vessels suspending the certificate of registration, shall confiscate such`
  line `certificate and return the certificate to the owner or master only upon withdrawal of the order of`
  line suspension.
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (63992)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Cancellation of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=63992&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any mechanically propelled inland vessel registered under`
  line `this Act is declared missing, destroyed, lost, abandoned or has been rendered permanently unfit for`
  line `service or destined for scrapping or dismantling or sold abroad; the owner of the vessel shall, within such`
  line `time as may be prescribed by the Central Government, report the fact to the Registrar of Inland Vessels of`
  line `the place where the vessel is registered and shall also forward to that authority, along with the report, the`
  line `certificate of registration of the vessel and thereupon such Registrar of Inland Vessels shall have the`
  line `certificate of registration cancelled.`
  line
  line `(2) Any Registrar of Inland Vessels may at any time require that any mechanically propelled inland`
  line `vessel within the local limits of his jurisdiction may be inspected by such designated authority as the State`
  line `Government may, by general or special order, appoint in this behalf and, if as a result of such inspection,`
  line `such Registrar of Inland Vessels is satisfied that the vessel is in such a condition that it is not fit to ply in`
  line `any inland water, the Registrar of Inland Vessels may, after giving the owner of the vessel an opportunity`
  line `of being heard, cancel the registration of the vessel and require the owner thereof to surrender forthwith to`
  line `him, the certificate of registration in respect of that vessel, if it has not already been so surrendered.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (63993)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Mortgage of mechanically propelled inland vessel or share therein.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=63993&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) A registered`
  line `mechanically propelled inland vessel or a share therein may be mortgaged as a security for a loan or other`
  line `valuable consideration, and the instrument creating the security shall be in such form, as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Central Government, and on the production of such instrument, the Registrar of Inland`
  line `Vessels who granted the certificate of registration shall record it in the book of registry.`
  line
  line `(2) The manner and the conditions, subject to which a mechanically propelled inland vessel or a share`
  line `therein may be mortgaged, shall be such as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (63994)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Training and minimum age for employment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=63994&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) The standards for qualification, training,`
  line `training institutes, examination and grant of certificate of competency for the purposes of this Chapter`
  line `shall be such as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) No person under the age of eighteen years shall be employed on a mechanically propelled inland`
  line `vessel registered under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (63995)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Minimum manning scale and manning requirements.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=63995&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `The minimum manning scale`
  line `applicable to different class or category of mechanically propelled inland vessels, categorised under this`
  line `Act or such other laws for the time being in force in India, shall be such as may be prescribed by the`
  line `Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (63996)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Appointment and duties of examiners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=63996&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may appoint examiners, in`
  line `accordance with the criteria and qualifications, as may be prescribed by the Central Government, for the`
  line `purpose of examining the qualifications of persons desirous of obtaining certificates under this Chapter to`
  line `the effect that they are competent to undertake the responsibilities of and act as, masters, or as engineers`
  line `or engine-drivers, or as such other persons, as the case may be, on the mechanically propelled inland`
  line vessels.
  line
  line `(2) The examiners shall evaluate the persons who have undergone the training required for qualifying`
  line `as masters, or as engineers or engine-drivers, or as such other persons, as the case may be, and shall report`
  line `the list of successful candidates who possess the required qualifications to the Central Government or`
  line `such other officer appointed or authorised by notification by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (63997)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Grant of certificate of competency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=63997&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may evaluate the report`
  line `provided by the examiners, and upon confirmation as to the correctness of such report; shall grant to`
  line `every candidate; who is reported by the examiners to possess the required qualifications, with the`
  line `certificate of competency, certifying that the candidate specified in the report is competent to serve, in such`
  line `capacity as may be specified therein, on any class or category or whole of the mechanically propelled inland vessel`
  line `as specified in the certificate.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government shall require for further examination or a re-examination of all or any of`
  line `the candidates, if it is found that the report submitted by examiners is defective, or there exists reason to`
  line `believe that such a report has been unduly made.`
  line
  line `(3) The certificate of competency shall be in such form and manner as may be prescribed by the`
  line `Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (63998)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Certificate of service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=63998&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, on an application, without examination,`
  line `grant a certificate of service to any person who has served as a master, or as an engineer, of a vessel of the`
  line `Coast Guard, Indian Navy or regular Army for such period as may be prescribed in this behalf by the`
  line `Central Government, to the effect that he is competent to act, as a first-class master, second-class master`
  line `or serang, or as an engineer, first-class engine-driver or second-class engine-driver or in such capacity as`
  line `may be specified therein, as the case may be, on board the mechanically propelled inland vessel.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of granting of certificate of service under sub-section (1), the State Government`
  line `shall verify the certificate, certifying the competence of the applicant as issued by the Coast Guard, Indian`
  line `Navy or regular Army, as submitted to it by such applicant along with his application.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained herein, the State Government may by recording reasons`
  line `thereof, refuse granting of certificate of service under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(4) A certificate of service so granted under sub-section (1), shall be in such form and manner; and`
  line `shall be subject to such conditions, as may be prescribed by the Central Government, and shall have the`
  line `same effect as a certificate of competency granted under section 37.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (63999)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Effect of certificate of competency or certificate of service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=63999&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this`
  line `Act and such conditions as may be prescribed by the Central Government, a certificate of competency or`
  line `certificate of service shall be valid throughout India.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (64000)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Suspension and cancellation of certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64000&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the holder of any certificate issued under this`
  line `Chapter is found to have acted in contravention to the provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder;`
  line `the said certificate shall be liable to be suspended or cancelled.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government or any officer appointed or authorised under this Chapter shall issue notice`
  line `to the holder of certificate and shall provide him an opportunity of being heard before suspension or`
  line `cancellation of certificates issued under this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2), the State Government or any officer`
  line `appointed or authorised under this Chapter, may suspend or cancel the certificate of competency or the`
  line `certificate of service granted under this Chapter by recording reasons thereof.`
  line
  line `(4) If a certificate issued under the provisions of this Chapter is suspended or cancelled, the holder of`
  line `such certificate shall deliver it to the State Government or such officer, appointed or authorised by that`
  line `Government by notification in Official Gazette under this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (64001)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Registry of certificate holders and central registry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64001&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government shall maintain`
  line `registers in electronic format to record, the details and data of the certificate, and the respective`
  line `certificates, issued under this Chapter in such form and manner as may be prescribed by it.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government shall report and update the Central Government with the information on`
  line `data and details of certificates issued, granted, cancelled or suspended or such other remarks, made by the`
  line `respective authority in regular intervals, as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government shall update the central data base with the reports and information`
  line `received from all the State Governments under this Chapter in electronic format.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (64002)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Special category vessels.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64002&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of this Chapter, the Central Government may, by`
  line `rules to be made in this behalf, specify the criteria and standards to identify any class or category of`
  line `mechanically propelled inland vessels as special category vessels based on their design, construction, use,`
  line `purpose, area of plying, source of energy or fuelling, or any other criteria or standards.`
  line
  line `(2) The requirements of construction, design, survey, registration, manning, qualification,`
  line `competency, or the requirements in addition to those contained elsewhere in this Act shall be such, as`
  line `may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Governments shall identify the mechanically propelled inland vessels as special`
  line `category vessels based on the criteria and standards prescribed by the Central Government under subsection (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (64003)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Appointment or authorisation of officers to implement provisions, grant certificate of fitness, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64003&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government shall appoint or authorise such number of officers for the`
  line `purpose of performing duties and implementing the provisions of this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) On an application made by owner, operator or master of any mechanically propelled inland vessel`
  line `in such form as may be prescribed by the State Government, any officer appointed or authorised under`
  line `sub-section (1), on being satisfied that such vessel complies with the provisions of this Act and falls under`
  line `the special category vessels as identified in this Chapter, and subject to such other conditions including`
  line `validity as may be prescribed by the State Government, may grant a certificate of fitness, in such form`
  line `and manner as may be prescribed by that Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The officer appointed or authorised under sub-section (1) may, for reasons to be recorded in`
  line `writing, refuse to grant the certificate of fitness in respect of an application made under sub-section (2).`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (64004)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Safety of passengers or service users.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64004&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) The safety features, gears and such other measures`
  line `by which any mechanically propelled inland vessel, identified as special category vessel under this`
  line `Chapter, shall comply with and be equipped in accordance with the categorisation of such vessel, shall be`
  line `such as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The maximum carrying capacity of the vessel identified as special category vessel by specifying`
  line `the safety loadline or the limits of loadline to keep them afloat, or such other criteria and conditions, other`
  line `than those mentioned elsewhere in this Act for the safe voyage of such inland vessel, shall be such as may`
  line `be prescribed by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (64005)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Inspection of vessel.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64005&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) The surveyor may, other than for the purpose of survey, at any`
  line `reasonable time, go on board any special category vessel, and inspect the respective vessel including the`
  line `hull, equipment and machinery or any part or properties of such vessel.`
  line
  line `(2) The owner, operator, agent, master and any such person in-charge of the special category vessel,`
  line `shall make available all necessary facilities to the surveyor for inspection and survey, and all such`
  line `information regarding the vessel and her machinery and equipment, or any part thereof, respectively, as`
  line `the surveyor or such other officer may reasonably require.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (64006)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Suspension or cancellation of certificate of fitness.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64006&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any special category vessel does not`
  line `comply with the provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder, the State Government may issue`
  line `notice to the owner or operator or master or any person in-charge of such vessel, for rectifying the noncompliance within such time as may be specified therein.`
  line
  line `(2) In case of continuance of non-compliance by the owner or operator or master or any person incharge of the special category vessel even after receipt of the notice issued under sub-section (1), the State`
  line `Government may, after providing an opportunity of being heard and for reasons to be recorded in writing,`
  line `suspend or cancel the certificate of fitness issued to such vessel under this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(3) If the certificate of fitness of a special category vessel has been suspended or cancelled under subsection (2), then such vessel shall cease to operate till the suspension is revoked, or in the event of`
  line `cancellation, shall cease to operate till a new certificate of fitness is granted.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (64007)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Navigation safety, lights and signals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64007&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) The specifications and requirements of signals and`
  line `equipment based on classification and categorisation of mechanically propelled vessels, to be complied`
  line `with by such vessels shall be such as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The fog and distress signals to be carried and used, the steering and sailing rules to be complied`
  line `with and the different protocols for exhibition and display of different standards of lights, shapes and`
  line `signals, by any mechanically propelled vessel plying in inland waters shall be such, as may be prescribed`
  line `by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The owner or master of every mechanically propelled vessel, while in the inland water limit, shall`
  line `comply with the rules made under sub-sections (1) and (2), and shall not carry or exhibit any lights or`
  line `shapes or use any fog or distress signals, other than that required to be exhibited under this Chapter or the`
  line `rules made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (64008)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Obligation to ensure safe navigation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64008&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every mechanically propelled vessel shall adopt`
  line `necessary measures to prevent collision and to ensure safe navigation through inland waters.`
  line
  line `(2) If any damage to person or property arises in the inland water limit due to non-observance of any`
  line `of the rules made under this Chapter by any mechanically propelled vessel, the damage shall be deemed`
  line `to have been occasioned by the wilful default of the person in-charge of such vessel at that time, unless it`
  line `is shown to the satisfaction of the court that the circumstances of the case demanded deviance from the`
  line `applicable rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (64009)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Distress signal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64009&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `The master of a mechanically propelled vessel, while in the inland water limit,`
  line `on finding or encountering a dangerous derelict or any other hazard to navigation in the inland waterways,`
  line `shall immediately send a signal to indicate the danger or distress, or any such information to other`
  line `mechanically propelled vessels in the vicinity and to the concerned State Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that no fees or charges shall be levied on any mechanically propelled vessel, in using any`
  line `device for communicating any information under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (64010)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Assistance to vessels in distress and persons in distress.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64010&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1) The master of any mechanically`
  line `propelled vessel, while in the inland water limit, who has received any signal of distress from any vessel`
  line `or aircraft within the inland water limit, shall proceed immediately to the assistance of the persons in`
  line `distress by acknowledging the receipt of such signal to the vessel in distress..`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the master of a mechanically propelled`
  line `vessel shall be released from the obligation to render assistance as provided in the said sub-section, if he`
  line `is unable to do so, or in the special circumstances of the case, considers it unreasonable to act as provided`
  line `in the said sub-section, or if the requirement for assistance is being complied with by other vessels, or the`
  line `assistance is no longer required..`
  line
  line `(3) The master of any mechanically propelled vessel, while in the inland water limit, shall render`
  line `assistance to every person found in danger of being lost in the inland waters..`
  line
  line `(4) The master of any mechanically propelled inland vessel may abstain from complying with subsection (3), if in his judgment, he is unable to or, in the special circumstances of the case, such assistance`
  line `may not be rendered without serious danger to his vessel, or to the persons on board and, in such event`
  line `shall inform the respective authorities regarding his inability of such non-compliance.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (64011)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Life saving, fire safety and communication appliances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64011&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, by`
  line `rules made in this behalf, specify the class or category of mechanically propelled inland vessels to be`
  line `equipped with navigation aids, life saving appliances, fire detection and extinguishing appliances and`
  line `communication appliances.`
  line
  line `(2) The owner, operator or master of all mechanically propelled inland vessels shall comply with the`
  line `requirements of navigation aids, life saving appliances, fire detection and extinguishing appliances and`
  line `communication appliances as specified in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) The State Government may appoint or authorise such officers as surveyors to inspect and ensure`
  line `that the mechanically propelled inland vessels comply with the applicable requirements specified in subsection (1).`
  line
  line `(4) If the surveyor, on inspection, finds that the mechanically propelled inland vessel is not so`
  line `provided with life saving and fire appliances in conformity with the provisions of this Act and the rules`
  line `made thereunder, he shall issue a notice to the master or owner or operator in writing pointing out the`
  line `deficiency, and unless the master or owner or operator complies with the said notice and report such`
  line `compliance to the surveyor, the said vessel shall not proceed to conduct any voyage.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (64012)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Chemicals, etc., to be designated as pollutants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64012&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, by`
  line `notification, designate the list of chemicals, any ingredients or substance carried as bunker or as cargo, or`
  line `any substance in any form discharged from any mechanically propelled inland vessel, as pollutants.`
  line
  line `(2) The owner or master of any mechanically propelled inland vessel shall discharge or dispose of the`
  line `sewage and garbage in accordance with such standards and manner as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(3) No mechanically propelled inland vessel shall cause pollution by discharging or dumping of`
  line `pollutants designated under sub-section (1):`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall apply to the discharge dump or emission of such oil or`
  line `oily mixture, hazardous chemical or obnoxious substance or any other pollutant, as the case may be, from`
  line `a mechanically propelled inland vessel for the purpose of securing the safety of any mechanically`
  line `propelled inland vessel, preventing damage to another mechanically propelled inland vessel, cargo or`
  line `saving of life at inland waters.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (64013)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Certificate of prevention of pollution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64013&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, by rules made in this`
  line `behalf, specify the standards of construction and equipment of the mechanically propelled inland vessels`
  line `to ensure compliance with the requirements of this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government shall appoint or authorise such officers to ensure construction, installation`
  line `and maintenance of equipment of all mechanically propelled inland vessels and issue certificate of`
  line `prevention of pollution, in compliance with the provisions of this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(3) Every mechanically propelled inland vessel, which has been constructed and equipped in`
  line `compliance with this Chapter shall be issued with a certificate of prevention of pollution in such form,`
  line `validity and content as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) Every mechanically propelled inland vessel shall carry on board a valid certificate of prevention`
  line `of pollution and shall furnish the same on demand by concerned officers appointed or authorised under`
  line `this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (64014)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Reception facilities and containment of pollution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64014&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, by rules`
  line `made in this behalf, specify the conditions for construction, use and maintenance of reception facilities for`
  line `the containment of pollution and removal of pollutants arising from spillage or discharge arising from`
  line `mechanically propelled inland vessels at all cargo terminals or passenger terminals.`
  line
  line `(2) The owner or operator of all cargo terminals or passenger terminals shall provide reception`
  line `facilities to discharge oil, oily mixture, hazardous chemicals, sewage or obnoxious substances at such`
  line `cargo or passenger terminal, as the case may be, in compliance of sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) The owner or operator of all cargo terminals or passenger terminals, providing reception facilities`
  line `shall receive charges, at such rates as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(4) For the purposes of minimising the pollution already caused, or for preventing the imminent threat`
  line `of pollution, the Central Government or such other officer appointed by the State Government may, by`
  line `order in writing, direct the owner or operator of cargo or passenger terminal to provide or arrange for the`
  line `provision of such pollution containment equipment and pollutant removing materials, at such cargo and`
  line `passenger terminal, as may be specified in such order.`
  line
  line `(5) The owner or operator of the passenger or cargo terminal shall submit a report of compliance to`
  line `the Central Government or such other officer appointed under sub-section (4), in such form as may be`
  line `prescribed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(6) The owner, operator or master of any mechanically propelled vessel used or plying within inland`
  line `waters, shall discharge the pollutants at the port reception facilities in such manner as may be prescribed`
  line `by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (64015)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Appointment of surveyor or officer to inspect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64015&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may appoint or`
  line `authorise such officers as surveyors to inspect any cargo or passenger terminal lying within its respective`
  line jurisdiction.
  line
  line `(2) The surveyor authorised under sub-section (1) may, at any reasonable time, enter and inspect any`
  line `cargo or passenger terminal to—`
  line
  line `(a) ensure that the provisions of this Chapter are complied with;`
  line
  line `(b) verify whether such cargo or passenger terminal is equipped for pollution containment and`
  line `removal, in conformity with the order of the State Government or any of the rules made under this`
  line `Chapter; and`
  line
  line `(c) satisfy himself of the adequacy of the measures taken to prevent pollution.`
  line
  line `(3) If the surveyor, on inspection, finds that the cargo or passenger terminal is not provided with the`
  line `required pollution containment equipment and pollutant removing materials, he shall give a notice in`
  line `writing pointing out the deficiencies and the recommended remedial measures to rectify such deficiency,`
  line `that is identified during the inspection, to the owner or operator of such cargo or passenger terminal, as`
  line `the case may be.`
  line
  line `(4) No owner or operator of such cargo or passenger terminal, as the case may be, served with the`
  line `notice under sub-section (3), shall proceed with any work at such cargo or passenger terminal, until he`
  line `obtains a certificate signed by the surveyor to the effect that the cargo or passenger terminal, is properly`
  line `provided with the required pollution containment equipment and pollutant removing materials in`
  line `conformity with the rules made under this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (64016)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Investigation into incidents of pollution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64016&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government shall direct any designated`
  line `authority or such other authorised officer appointed under Chapter XIII to conduct investigation into`
  line `incidents of pollution.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government shall update the Central Government with such information or report of the`
  line `court, if so directed by such court concerned, on incidents of pollution that occurs within its jurisdiction.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (64017)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Prohibition against intentionally causing wreck.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64017&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `The owner, operator, master or person incharge of a vessel plying in inland waters shall not intentionally abandon, desert, dump, throw overboard`
  line `or jettison the vessel or property or parts or cargo, so as to cause wreck.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (64018)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Receivers of wreck.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64018&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by notification, appoint or authorise any`
  line `officer to act as receiver of wreck within the respective jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `(2) The owner, operator, master or person in-charge of vessel, property or cargo, which is wrecked,`
  line `stranded or in distress or who has found any vessel, property or cargo wrecked, stranded or in distress in`
  line `the inland waters, shall immediately inform, by all means of communication to the receiver of wreck in`
  line `whose jurisdiction the vessel, property or cargo is found to be wrecked, stranded or in distress.`
  line
  line `(3) The owner of the wreck, whose property or cargo, is wrecked or stranded or is in distress in the`
  line `inland waters shall inform the receiver of wreck in writing of the finding thereof and of the marks by`
  line `which such wreck can be distinguished, and in cases, where the wreck is in possession of any person other`
  line `than the owner, operator, master or person in-charge of vessel, property or cargo, such person shall`
  line `deliver such wreck to the receiver of wreck.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this Chapter, the word person shall have the meaning assigned to`
  line `it in clause (42) of section 3 of the General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897).`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (64019)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Powers of Central Government to make rules for Chapter X.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64019&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of this`
  line `Chapter, the—.`
  line
  line `(a) powers and functions of the receiver of wreck;.`
  line
  line `(b) responsibilities and obligations of the owner, operator, master or person in-charge of vessel,`
  line `property or cargo with respect to the wreck;.`
  line
  line `(c) measures adopted for the removal of obstruction to navigation;.`
  line
  line `(d) disposal of wreck, including its sale and proceeds of unsold property;.`
  line
  line `(e) measures to be adopted for protection of wreck, fouling of government moorings;.`
  line
  line `(f) rights and duties of salvors and performance of salvage operations or resolution of disputes`
  line `pertaining to amount payable to salvors; and.`
  line
  line `(g) such other matter, which the Central Government may deem necessary for the efficient`
  line `administration and removal of wrecks, shall be such as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (64020)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Liability under Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64020&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `(1) The owner, operator, master, a member of crew or an insurer shall be`
  line `liable for the offences and contraventions of the provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any person is beneficially interested otherwise than by way of mortgage or in the share in`
  line `any mechanically propelled inland vessel registered in the name of some other person as owner, the`
  line `person so interested, and the registered owner, shall be liable to all the pecuniary penalties imposed by`
  line `this or any other Act on the owners of mechanically propelled inland vessels or shares therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (64021)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Apportionment of loss.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64021&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever by the fault of two or more mechanically propelled`
  line `inland vessels, damage or loss is caused to one or more of them or to the cargo of one or more of them or`
  line `to any property on board one or more of them, the liability to make good the damage or loss shall be in`
  line `proportion to the degree in which each of such vessel was at fault:`
  line
  line `Provided that---`
  line
  line `(a) if, having regard to all the circumstances of the case, it is not possible to establish different`
  line `degrees of fault, the liability shall be apportioned equally;`
  line
  line `(b) nothing in this section shall operate so as to render any vessel liable for any loss or damage to`
  line `which such vessel has not contributed;`
  line
  line `(c) nothing in this section shall affect the liability of any person under any contract, or shall be`
  line `construed as imposing any liability upon any person from which he is exempted by any contract or by the provisions of any law for the time being in force, or as affecting the right of any person to limit`
  line `his liability in the manner provided by such law.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this Chapter, reference to damage or loss caused by the fault of a mechanically`
  line `propelled inland vessel shall be construed as including reference to any salvage or other expenses,`
  line `consequent upon that fault, recoverable under the provisions of any law for the time being in force by way`
  line `of damages.`
  line
  line `(3) The person who has suffered damage or injured or his representative may apply to any court`
  line `having appropriate jurisdiction on the claim, for the detention or attachment of the vessel.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (64022)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Liability for personal injury, loss of life or pollution to environment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64022&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, loss of life`
  line `or personal injuries is suffered, damage to property or pollution is caused by any person on any`
  line `mechanically propelled inland vessel or any other vessel, owing to the fault of that vessel and of any other`
  line `vessel or vessels, the liability of the owners of such vessels concerned shall be joint and several.`
  line
  line `(2) No liability for any claim other than loss of life, personal injury or pollution, shall attach to the`
  line `owner, operator, master, or a member of crew or insurer under this Chapter, if he proves that the cause for`
  line claim---
  line
  line `(a) was a result of an act of war, hostility, civil war, insurrection or a natural phenomenon of an`
  line `exceptional, inevitable and irresistible character; or`
  line
  line `(b) was wholly caused by an act or omission with intent to cause such damage by any other`
  line `person; or`
  line
  line `(c) was wholly caused by the negligence or other wrongful act of a State Government or other`
  line `authority responsible for the maintenance of lights or other navigational aids in exercise of its`
  line `functions in that behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (64023)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 63
  title `Detention of mechanically propelled inland vessel.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64023&sectionno=63&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `The State Government may appoint or`
  line `authorise any officer under this Chapter, for the purpose of detaining any mechanically propelled inland`
  line `vessel in connection with a claim, or an offence under this Chapter, and the procedure thereof shall be`
  line `such as may be prescribed by that Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (64024)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 64
  title `Limitation of liability.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64024&sectionno=64&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `(1) The owner, operator, master or any person in-charge of a vessel or`
  line `member of crew of any mechanically propelled vessel may limit the extent of his liability for---`
  line
  line `(a) claims in respect of loss of life or personal injury, or loss of, or damage to, property including`
  line `damage to jetties, wharfs, harbour basins and waterways and aids to navigation, occurring on board or`
  line `in direct connection with the operation of such vessels or with salvage operations, and consequential`
  line `loss resulting therefrom;`
  line
  line `(b) claims arising out of loss resulting from delay in the carriage of cargo and passengers or their`
  line `luggage by inland waters;`
  line
  line `(c) claims arising out of other loss resulting from infringement of rights other than contractual`
  line `rights, occurring in direct connection with the operation of such vessel or salvage operations;`
  line
  line `(d) claims in respect of the raising, removal, destruction or rendering harmless of a vessel or the`
  line `cargo which is sunk, wrecked, stranded or abandoned;`
  line
  line `(e) claims of a person, other than the person liable, in respect of measures taken by such person in`
  line `order to avert or minimise loss and for further loss caused by such measure;`
  line
  line `(f)claims for the loss of life or personal injury to passengers of such vessel brought by or on behalf of any person---`
  line
  line `(i) under the contract of passenger carriage; or`
  line
  line `(ii) who, with the consent of the carrier, is accompanying a vessel for live animals which`
  line `are covered by a contract for the carriage of goods, carried in such vessel.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, no person shall be entitled to limit his liability`
  line for---
  line
  line `(a) claims for salvage; or`
  line
  line `(b) claims stipulated as exempted from the application of limitation of liability under any other`
  line `law for the time being in force in India.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, the act of invoking limitation of liability shall`
  line `not be construed as constituting an admission of liability by any person who takes the defence.`
  line
  line `(4) For the purposes of this Chapter, the liability of the owner or operator of a mechanically propelled`
  line `inland vessel shall include the liability in an action brought against such vessels.`
  line
  line `(5) The limits of liability and the criteria in determining compensation for any claim as provided`
  line `under sub-section (1) shall be such as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(6) The person entitled to limit liability under sub-section (1) may apply to the High Court of`
  line `respective jurisdiction for constituting a limitation fund for the consolidated rate as provided for under`
  line `this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(7) Where a vessel or other property is detained in connection with a claim, covered under this`
  line `Chapter, the High Court may order release of such vessel or other property, upon an application made by`
  line `the person, who is entitled to limit their liability and by---`
  line
  line `(a) ensuring that such person, who is entitled to constitute the limitation fund has submitted his`
  line `availability in person to the jurisdiction of the High Court; or`
  line
  line `(b) depositing sufficient fund or financial guarantee as determined by the High Court as security;`
  line or
  line
  line `(c) constituting the limitation fund, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (64025)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 65
  title `Non-applicability of limitation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64025&sectionno=65&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `No person shall be entitled to limit the liability against any`
  line `claim, if such claim has arisen due to intentional act or negligence of the person or his employee, who`
  line `otherwise would have been entitled to limit his liability under this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (64026)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 66
  title `Insurance to cover.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64026&sectionno=66&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `No mechanically propelled vessel shall be used for voyage in inland`
  line `waters, unless there is in force—`
  line
  line `(a) a policy of insurance which shall cover liability that may be incurred by the insured—`
  line
  line `(i) in respect of the death of or bodily injury to any person or damage to any property caused`
  line `by or arising out of the use of the mechanically propelled vessel;`
  line
  line `(ii) in respect of liability of operational pollution and accidental pollution of inland waters;`
  line
  line `(b) a policy of insurance in compliance of the Public Liability Insurance Act, 1991 (6 of 1991), if`
  line `the mechanically propelled inland vessel is carrying or meant to carry, dangerous or hazardous goods;`
  line
  line `(c) a policy of insurance covering the mechanically propelled vessel to—`
  line
  line `(i) a value not less than the liability incurred; or`
  line
  line `(ii) entitle it to be covered under limitation of liability as provided under this Act, a value not`
  line `less than the specified and applicable limitation amount:`
  line
  line `Provided that any policy of insurance issued with a value not less than the limitation of liability in`
  line `force, immediately before the commencement of this Act, shall continue to be effective for a period`
  line `of twelve months after such commencement or till the date of expiry of such policy, whichever is`
  line earlier.
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (64027)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 67
  title `Contractual liability not to cover.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64027&sectionno=67&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Chapter, a`
  line `policy shall not be required to cover any contractual liability of the insured that arises due to any`
  line `performance or non-performance of a contract or of agreement in the capacity of a service provider`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (64028)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 68
  title `Issuance and terms of insurance policy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64028&sectionno=68&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of section 66, the policy of`
  line `insurance issued shall be a policy, which—`
  line
  line `(a) is issued by an authorised insurer;`
  line
  line `(b) insures the mechanically propelled inland vessel, any person or any classes of persons`
  line `specified in the policy to the extent specified in section 66; and`
  line
  line `(c) is a certificate of insurance issued by the insurer to the insured in such form and content, and`
  line `subject to such conditions as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The terms and conditions to be incorporated in the contract of insurance entered between insurer`
  line `and insured to cover the risks as provided in section 66 shall be such as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (64029)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 69
  title `Duty to indemnify and direct action against insurer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64029&sectionno=69&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained`
  line `in any law for the time being in force, an insurer issuing a policy of insurance under this section shall be`
  line `liable to indemnify the insured or any person, as specified in the policy in respect of any liability which`
  line `the policy purports to cover in the case of the insured or that person.`
  line
  line `(2) Any claim for compensation against the loss or damage under this Act and covered by the`
  line `insurance may be brought directly against the insurer in respect of the liability incurred by the registered`
  line owner.
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (64030)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 70
  title `Effect of death on certain causes of action.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64030&sectionno=70&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in section`
  line `306 of the Indian Succession Act, 1925 (39 of 1925), the death of a person in whose favour a certificate of`
  line `insurance had been issued, if it occurs after the happening of an event which has given rise to a claim`
  line `under the provisions of this Chapter, shall not be a bar to the survival of any cause of action arising out of`
  line `the said event against his estate or against the insurer.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (64031)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 71
  title `Effect of certificate of insurance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64031&sectionno=71&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `When an insurer has issued a certificate of insurance in`
  line `respect of a contract of insurance between the insurer and the insured person, then,—`
  line
  line `(a) if and so long as the policy described in the certificate has not been issued by the insurer to the`
  line `insured, the insurer shall, as between himself and any other person except the insured, be deemed to`
  line `have issued to the insured person a policy of insurance conforming in all respects with the description`
  line `and particulars stated in such certificate; and`
  line
  line `(b) if the insurer has issued to the insured the policy described in the certificate, but the actual`
  line `terms of the policy are less favourable to the person claiming under or by virtue of the policy against`
  line `the insurer either directly or through the insured than the particulars of the policy as stated in the`
  line `certificate, the policy shall, as between the insurer and any other person except the insured, be`
  line `deemed to be in terms conforming in all respects with the particulars stated in the said certificate.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (64032)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 72
  title `Transfer of certificate of insurance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64032&sectionno=72&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `Where a person in whose favour the certificate of`
  line `insurance has been issued in accordance with the provisions of this Chapter transfers to another person,`
  line `the ownership of the mechanically propelled vessel covered under this Chapter, in respect of which such`
  line `insurance was taken together with the policy of insurance relating thereto, the certificate of insurance and`
  line `the policy described in the certificate shall be deemed to have been transferred in favour of the person to`
  line `whom the mechanically propelled inland vessel is transferred with effect from the date of its transfer.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that such deemed transfer shall include`
  line `transfer of rights and liabilities covered under the said certificate of insurance and the policy of insurance.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (64033)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 73
  title `Powers of Central Government to make rules for Chapter XII.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64033&sectionno=73&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government`
  line `shall, by rules made in this behalf, specify the terms, conditions and procedures to be complied with by`
  line `the insurers and insured including—`
  line
  line `(a) cover note of insurance and its validity;`
  line
  line `(b) rights and duties of the insured;`
  line
  line `(c) procedures and processes involved in processing of claims;`
  line
  line `(d) duties and obligations of the insurers to satisfy the judgments and awards;`
  line
  line `(e) rights of claimants, liability of the insured and the insurers in special circumstances such as`
  line `the insured becomes insolvent and the procedures to be followed;`
  line
  line `(f) procedures, processes and minimum terms of conditions for the settlement between the`
  line `insurers and insured persons;`
  line
  line `(g) procedures to be followed in the transfer of certificate of insurance; and`
  line
  line `(h) such other matters directly or indirectly related to insurance of mechanically propelled`
  line `vessels, for the purposes of effective implementation and administration of this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (64034)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 74
  title `Reporting of casualty, accident, wreck, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64034&sectionno=74&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government, may by notification,`
  line `appoint any designated authority for the purposes of this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) The owner, operator or master of a mechanically propelled inland vessel, shall give information of`
  line `any wreck, abandonment, damage, casualty, accident, explosion or loss occurred to or on board such a`
  line `vessel while in the inland waters, to the officer in-charge of the nearest police station and to the`
  line `designated authority appointed under sub-section (1), in such form and manner as may be prescribed by`
  line `the State Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The designated authority shall at once report the contents of the information referred to in subsection (2) to the District Magistrate.`
  line
  line `(4) The officer in-charge of the police station shall, on receipt of information referred to in subsection (2), investigate into the matter and submit a report to the jurisdictional Judicial Magistrate in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of Chapter XII of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  line
  line `(5) The Judicial Magistrate may, on receiving the report referred to in sub-section (4), take action as`
  line `he may deem fit in accordance with the provisions of Chapter XVI.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (64035)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 75
  title `Preliminary enquiry by designated authority and inquiry by District Magistrate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64035&sectionno=75&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `designated authority may, in pursuance of the information referred to in sub-section (2) of section 74,`
  line `conduct a preliminary enquiry and submit a report thereof to the District Magistrate, who shall transmit`
  line `the same to the concerned State Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may, on receipt of the report referred to in sub-section (1), if deemed`
  line `necessary, direct the District Magistrate to submit an additional report to it and send a copy thereof to the`
  line `Judicial Magistrate of the first class referred to in sub-section (4) of section 74 through the jurisdictional`
  line police.
  line
  line `(3) The powers of the District Magistrate referred to in sub-section (2) and the procedures to be`
  line `followed by him in holding the inquiry for submission of additional report shall be such as may be`
  line `prescribed by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (64036)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 76
  title Assessors.
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64036&sectionno=76&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of this Chapter, the State Government may appoint and`
  line `maintain a list of assessors, which may be revised from time to time.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government shall, by rules made in this behalf, specify the qualifications, criteria and`
  line `consideration, fees or charges for the assessors, who are conversant with the maritime affairs and have experience in the merchant service or in the navigation of the mechanically propelled inland vessels and`
  line `willing to act as an assessor.`
  line
  line `(3) The District Magistrate may, for the purposes of assisting in the inquiry under this Chapter,`
  line `appoint any number of assessors, from the list of assessors provided to him by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(4) In every inquiry, other than the one specified in sub-section (3), the District Magistrate may, if he`
  line `thinks fit, appoint an assessor, for the purposes of such inquiry, any person.`
  line
  line `(5) Every person appointed as an assessor under this section shall assist the District Magistrate in the`
  line `inquiry and deliver his opinion as may be sought for, which shall be recorded in the proceedings.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (64037)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 77
  title `Report of District Magistrate to be notified by State Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64037&sectionno=77&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `(1) The District`
  line `Magistrate shall, in the case of every inquiry under this Chapter, make a full report of the conclusions at`
  line `which he has arrived, together with the evidence recorded and the written opinion of any assessor.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government shall, on receipt of the report referred to in sub-section (1) from the District`
  line `Magistrate, cause it to be published by notification in its Official Gazette.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (64038)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 78
  title `Powers of District Magistrate subsequent to inquiry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64038&sectionno=78&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `(1) The District Magistrate may, after`
  line `inquiry, recommend in his report for cancellation or suspension or confiscation of a certificate of`
  line `competency or a certificate of service granted to a master, crew or engineer by the State Government`
  line `under Chapter VI, if such District Magistrate finds that—`
  line
  line `(a) the accident or casualty, including loss, stranding or abandonment of, or damage to, any`
  line `mechanically propelled inland vessel, or loss of life, has been caused by the wrongful act or default of`
  line `such master or engineer;`
  line
  line `(b) such master or engineer is incompetent or has been guilty of any gross act of drunkenness,`
  line `tyranny or other misconduct, or in a case of collision, has failed to render such assistance or give such`
  line `information or notice as may be required under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) At the conclusion of the inquiry, or as soon thereafter as possible, the District Magistrate shall`
  line `state in open sitting, the decision arrived at by him with respect to the cancellation or suspension or`
  line `confiscation of any certificate of competency or a certificate of service and, if suspension is ordered, the`
  line `period for which the certificate is suspended.`
  line
  line `(3) Without prejudice to the provisions of this section, the District Magistrate may also make such`
  line `order and require such security in respect of the costs of the matter as he may deem fit and necessary in`
  line `the circumstances of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (64039)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 79
  title `Power of State Government to suspend, cancel and confiscate certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64039&sectionno=79&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State`
  line `Government, in whose jurisdiction the certificate of competency or a certificate of service was granted`
  line `under Chapter VI, may cancel or suspend any such certificate or, in the event of the vessel being found in`
  line `the jurisdiction of another State Government, such State Government may confiscate the certificate, if,---`
  line
  line `(a) on any inquiry made under this Chapter, the District Magistrate reports for cancellation or`
  line `suspension or confiscation of that certificate under section 78; or`
  line
  line `(b) the holder of such certificate is proved to have been convicted of any non-bailable offence; or`
  line
  line `(c) the holder of such certificate is proved to have deserted his vessel or has absented himself`
  line `without leave and without sufficient reason, from his vessel or from his duty; or`
  line
  line `(d) in the case of a person holding any designation as provided by the certificate of competency`
  line `or certificate of service, is or has become, in the opinion of the State Government, unfit to act in such`
  line `designation, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) Every person whose certificate of competency or a certificate of service is suspended or cancelled`
  line `under this Chapter shall deliver it to such person as the State Government, which suspended or cancelled`
  line `it, may direct.`
  line
  line `(3) If any State Government cancels, suspends or confiscates the certificate of competency or a`
  line `certificate of service granted under Chapter VI, the proceedings and the fact of confiscation and`
  line `recommendation for suspension or cancellation, shall be reported to the State Government which has`
  line `originally issued, granted or endorsed such certificates.`
  line
  line `(4) The State Government may, at any time, revoke any order of suspension or cancellation or`
  line `confiscation which it may have made under this Chapter, or grant a certificate anew, for reasons to be`
  line `recorded in writing, to any person whose certificate it has so cancelled and such certificate granted anew,`
  line `shall have the same effect as a certificate of competency granted under this Act after examination.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (64040)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 80
  title `Powers of Central Government to protect interests of service providers and service users.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64040&sectionno=80&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, prescribe the minimum standards, terms and conditions to protect the`
  line `interests of service providers and service users and to ensure safety of such persons.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (64041)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 81
  title `Prohibited goods and dangerous goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64041&sectionno=81&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall, by notification,`
  line `declare the list of dangerous goods that may be carried subject to such conditions, as may be prescribed`
  line `by it, and prohibited goods that are prohibited from being carried on any class or category of`
  line `mechanically propelled inland vessels, while plying in the inland waters.`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (64042)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 82
  title `Trade permission and endorsement of certificates of foreign vessels.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64042&sectionno=82&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `(1) No vessel registered`
  line `in any country other than India shall be permitted to be used or employed for the purposes of, carriage of`
  line `goods, transportation of passengers, storage units, accommodation, floating units or for such other`
  line `purposes within the inland waters, unless such vessel has secured prior permission from the Central`
  line `Government for its use or employment for such purposes and subject to such terms and conditions as may`
  line `be prescribed by the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that, where the Central Government has entered or in the event of that Government entering`
  line `into bilateral or multilateral treaties pertaining to the inland navigation, whereby the permission is`
  line `provided to the vessels belonging to foreign countries to ply within inland waters of India, the Central`
  line `Government or the State Government, as the case may be, shall impose or apply such vessels belonging to`
  line `the foreign countries, with the same conditions to the service providers in India.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of sub-section (1), any certificate granted by any other foreign country in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of any law for the time being in force in that country corresponding to the`
  line `provisions as provided in Chapters IV, V and VI under this Act may, on payment of such fees as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Central Government, for the grant of a similar certificate or licence under this Act, be`
  line `endorsed by—`
  line
  line `(a) any State Government in India; or`
  line
  line `(b) with the general or special sanction and subject to such other terms and conditions of such`
  line `State Government, by any authority competent to grant a similar certificate under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Upon endorsement of any such certificate as provided in sub-section (2), it shall have effect for`
  line `such period and to such extent as may be prescribed by the Central Government and shall be treated as if`
  line `it had been granted under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (64043)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 83
  title Pilotage.
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64043&sectionno=83&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, specify the requirement of pilotage`
  line `in whole or part of inland waterways declared as national waterways.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may, by notification, specify the requirement of pilotage in whole or part`
  line `or any stretch of designated inland waterways or such passages that lie within the respective territory of`
  line `such State Governments and in respect of which the Central Government has not specified under`
  line `sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (64044)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 84
  title `Certified master to be deemed pilot under Act 15 of 1908.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64044&sectionno=84&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of`
  line `section 83, every master of any mechanically propelled inland vessel, who possesses a master's certificate`
  line `granted under this Act and in force, shall, in ports to which section 31 of the Indian Ports Act, 1908 has`
  line `been extended, be deemed, for the purposes of that section, to be the pilot of the mechanically propelled`
  line `inland vessel of which he is in-charge.`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (64045)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 85
  title `Vessel detention and forfeiture.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64045&sectionno=85&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `(1)The State Government or any officer authorised under this`
  line `Act may, detain, forfeit or remove from the inland waters, any mechanically propelled inland vessel,`
  line `which is required to be registered under the provisions of this Act, if found---`
  line
  line `(a) plying or being used in inland waters without a valid certificate of registration;`
  line
  line `(b) plying without a valid certificate of survey;`
  line
  line `(c) plying with passengers beyond the permitted carrying capacity;`
  line
  line `(d) to have not affixed the registration number assigned to such vessels as provided under this`
  line Act;
  line
  line `(e) not complying with the manning requirements under Chapter VI;`
  line
  line `(f) not complying with the provisions of Chapter VIII;`
  line
  line `(g) to act in contravention to the provisions of Chapter X;`
  line
  line `(h) not in compliance with the provisions of Chapter XII;`
  line
  line `(i) to carry dangerous goods or prohibited goods in contravention to the provisions of section 81`
  line `or the rules made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) The owner, operator or any such person recognised as responsible for the vessel under detention,`
  line `shall pay the respective and applicable fees and charges for the safe custody and maintenance of the`
  line `detained or forfeited vessel, which shall be pre-condition for release of the vessel and which if unpaid,`
  line `shall create a lien over such vessel to comply with the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Upon compliance with the provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder, and after`
  line `rectifying the mistakes that lead to detention, the State Government shall, without any unreasonable`
  line `delay, release the vessel and her custody to the owner, operator or any such person recognised as`
  line `responsible for the vessel under this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) Unless specifically provided elsewhere in this Act, the procedures for detention, formality, fees`
  line `and conditions to be followed and observed by the concerned officer or authority or court, appointed or`
  line `authorised or constituted under this Act, for the purpose of detaining a vessel, shall be such as may be`
  line `prescribed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(5) An officer so authorised to enter any vessel may, for the purpose of enforcing the order of`
  line `detention or forfeiture, call to his aid, any police officer or any other person authorised under this Act or`
  line `such other laws in force in India.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (64046)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 86
  title `Constitution of Development Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64046&sectionno=86&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `(1)There shall be a Fund constituted by the State`
  line `Government to be called the Development Fund, to be utilised for—`
  line
  line `(a) meeting emergency preparedness;`
  line
  line `(b) meeting containment of pollution caused by discharge of oil, mixtures, obnoxious substances,`
  line `chemicals and other noxious and harmful substances, to preserve and protect inland waters;`
  line
  line `(c) supporting, part or whole of expenses of owners or economically backward sector involved in`
  line `activities of trade and living depending solely on inland waters;`
  line
  line `(d) removal of unidentified wreck or obstruction affecting and impeding navigation; and`
  line
  line `(e) boosting up development works of inland water navigation with respect to safety and`
  line `convenience of conveyance.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of constitution of the Development Fund under sub-section (1), endeavour shall`
  line `be made to design schemes of contribution from—`
  line
  line `(a) the State Government;`
  line
  line `(b) stake holders;`
  line
  line `(c) the amount collected from sale of wreck or cargo or remains thereof after deducting the expenses incurred;`
  line
  line `(d) excess fund out of judicial sale of vessels or any property or cargo after meeting the expenses`
  line `incurred or set-off against the court to meet damages or functioning of the court or administrative`
  line `machinery; and`
  line
  line `(e) part or proportionate disbursement of fees collected by the respective State Government as`
  line `provided in this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (64047)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 87
  title `Offences and penalties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64047&sectionno=87&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever, contravenes any of the provisions of this Act, shall be`
  line `punishable with penalty as mentioned in the third column of the Table provided in sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(2) The classification of offences for contravention of the provisions of this Act and the`
  line `corresponding penalties therefor shall be as provided in the following Table, namely:--`
  line
  line `Section Offence`
  line
  line Penalty
  line
  line `(1) (2) (3)`
  line
  line `8 Any owner, operator or construction yard,`
  line `found guilty of construction, alteration or`
  line `modification of mechanically propelled inland`
  line `vessel in contravention of section 8.`
  line `Fine which may extend to ten thousand`
  line `rupees for every non-compliance found.`
  line
  line `14 (1) Owner, operator or master of any`
  line `mechanically propelled inland vessel, using`
  line `such vessel, without a valid certificate of`
  line `survey has acted in contravention of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 14.`
  line `Fine which may extend to ten thousand`
  line `rupees for the first offence and twentyfive thousand rupees for subsequent`
  line offences.
  line
  line `18 (1) Owner, operator or master of any`
  line `mechanically propelled inland vessel`
  line `proceeding on any voyage or use a`
  line `mechanically propelled inland vessel required`
  line `to be registered, for any service, without a`
  line `valid certificate of registration and in`
  line `contravention of sub-section (1) of section 18.`
  line `Fine which may extend to ten thousand`
  line `rupees for the first offence and fifty`
  line `thousand rupees for subsequent offences.`
  line
  line `19 (1) Owner or master who does not carry a valid`
  line `certificate of registration or not making the`
  line `same available for inspection, has acted in`
  line `contravention of sub-section (1) of section 19.`
  line `Fine which may extend to ten thousand`
  line `rupees for every non-compliance found.`
  line
  line `24 (3) Owner not displaying the official number on`
  line `the conspicuous part of a vessel has acted in`
  line `contravention of sub-section (3) of section 24.`
  line `Fine which may extend to ten thousand`
  line rupees.
  line
  line `27 Owner, operator or any person responsible for`
  line `the operation of the vessel, has acted in`
  line `contravention of section 27.`
  line `Fine which may extend to ten thousand`
  line `rupees for the first offence and twentyfive thousand rupees for subsequent`
  line offences.
  line
  line `28 (2) Owner, operator or master of any`
  line `mechanically propelled inland vessel not`
  line `registering the details of alterations that are`
  line `mandated to be registered as specified in subsection (2) of section 28.`
  line `Fine which may extend to ten thousand`
  line `rupees for the first offence and twentyfive thousand rupees for subsequent`
  line offences.
  line
  line `29 Owner or operator of any mechanically`
  line `propelled inland vessel, who does not comply`
  line `with the requirements or has acted in`
  line `contravention of section 29.`
  line `Fine which may extend to five hundred`
  line `rupees for every day of non-compliance.`
  line
  line `30 Owner of any mechanically propelled inland`
  line `vessel, has acted in contravention of`
  line `section 30.`
  line `Fine which may extend to ten thousand`
  line `rupees per day or imprisonment which`
  line `may extend to one year, or with both.`
  line
  line `32 (1) Owner of any mechanically propelled inland`
  line `vessel, has acted in contravention of subsection (1) of section 32.`
  line `Fine which may extend to five thousand`
  line `rupees for every day of non-compliance.`
  line
  line `34 (2) Owner or operator on whose vessel, persons`
  line `under the age of eighteen years are employed,`
  line `has acted in contravention of sub-section (2)`
  line `of section 34.`
  line `Fine which may extend to five thousand`
  line `rupees for every day of non-compliance`
  line `or imprisonment not exceeding six`
  line `months, or with both.`
  line
  line `35 Owner or operator of any mechanically`
  line `propelled inland vessel without complying`
  line `with the specified minimum manning scale`
  line `has acted in contravention to section 35.`
  line `Fine which may extend to ten thousand`
  line `rupees for the first offence and twentyfive thousand rupees for subsequent`
  line offences.
  line
  line `40 (1) and`
  line `(4)`
  line `The holders of certificate of competency, has`
  line `acted in contravention to the provisions of this`
  line `Act or not surrendered the suspended,`
  line `cancelled or varied certificate issued under`
  line `non-submission of suspended or cancelled`
  line certificates.
  line `Fine up to five thousand rupees per day`
  line `or imprisonment extending up to six`
  line `months, or with both.`
  line
  line `44 Owner or operator or any person responsible`
  line `for the operation of special category vessel,`
  line `which does not comply with the provisions of`
  line `Chapter VII.`
  line `Fine which may extend to ten thousand`
  line `rupees for every day of non-compliance`
  line `or imprisonment extending up to six`
  line `months, or with both.`
  line
  line `47 Owner, operator or master of any`
  line `mechanically propelled vessel registered,`
  line `recognised or identified under this Act, for not`
  line `equipping the vessels or exhibiting the lights`
  line `and signals specified under Chapter VIII.`
  line `Fine which may extend to ten thousand`
  line `rupees for the first offence and twentyfive thousand rupees for subsequent`
  line offences.
  line
  line `48 Owner, operator or master not ensuring safe`
  line `navigation or causing damage due to nonobservance of regulations.`
  line `Fine which may extend to twenty-five`
  line `thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `49 and`
  line `50 (1)`
  line `Owner, operator or master of any`
  line `mechanically propelled vessel plying in inland`
  line `waters abstaining from proceeding to render`
  line `assistance after answering to the distress`
  line signal.
  line `Fine which may extend to ten thousand`
  line rupees.
  line
  line `51 (2) The owner, operator or master of any`
  line `mechanically propelled inland vessel`
  line `proceeding to conduct any voyage without`
  line `complying with the requirements of`
  line `navigation aids, life-saving appliances, fire`
  line `detection and extinguishing appliances and`
  line `communication appliances as specified under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 51.`
  line `Fine which may extend up to fifty`
  line `thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `52 (2) and`
  line `(3)`
  line `The owner, operator or master of any`
  line `mechanically propelled vessel causing`
  line `pollution by discharging or dumping of`
  line `pollutants in inland waters.`
  line `Fine which may extend to fifty thousand`
  line rupees.
  line
  line `53 (4) The owner, operator or master of any`
  line `mechanically propelled vessel, who are`
  line `required under this Act to possess a valid`
  line `prevention of pollution certificate, plying or`
  line `using the vessel without the said valid`
  line certificate.
  line `Fine which may extend to twenty-five`
  line `thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `54 (2) and`
  line `(5)`
  line `The owner or operator of any reception`
  line `facility who does not comply with the`
  line `standards and obligations stipulated.`
  line `Fine which may extend to fifty thousand`
  line rupees.
  line
  line `55 (4) The owner or operator of the terminal who`
  line `operates without complying with the notice`
  line `issued under sub-section (4) of section 55.`
  line `Fine which may extend to ten thousand`
  line `rupees per day of non-compliance`
  line `beyond period of notice.`
  line
  line `57 Any owner, operator or any person who`
  line `intentionally cause wreck within inland`
  line waters.
  line `Fine amounting to fifty thousand rupees`
  line `and imprisonment which may extend to`
  line `three years.`
  line
  line `58 (2) Any person who is guilty of offence`
  line `committed by contravention of sub-section (2)`
  line `of section 58.`
  line `Fine which may extend to ten thousand`
  line rupees.
  line
  line `66 Any owner or master plying any mechanically`
  line `propelled inland vessel without a valid`
  line `insurance as provided under section 66.`
  line `Fine which may extend to ten thousand`
  line `rupees and detention of the vessel till`
  line `certificate of insurance is procured.`
  line
  line `74 (2) The owner, operator or master of any`
  line `mechanically propelled inland vessel not`
  line `complying with sub-section (2) of section 74.`
  line `Fine which may extend to ten thousand`
  line rupees.
  line
  line `79 (2) Any person who holds a certificate issued`
  line `under Chapter VI and fails to surrender`
  line `suspended or cancelled certificates.`
  line `Fine which may extend to ten thousand`
  line `rupees for every day of non-submission.`
  line
  line `80 Any person, in the capacity of a service`
  line `provider or a service user, who acts in`
  line `contravention of section 80.`
  line `Fine which may extend to fifty thousand`
  line rupees.
  line
  line `82 Master or operator of any foreign vessels`
  line `acting in contravention of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 82.`
  line `Fine which may extend to fifty thousand`
  line `rupees or imprisonment which may`
  line `extend to one year, or with both.`
  line
  line `83 Owner, operator or master of mechanically`
  line `propelled inland vessel, who does not comply`
  line `with the requirement of pilotage in`
  line `contravention of section 83.`
  line `Fine which may extend to fifty thousand`
  line `rupees or imprisonment which may`
  line `extend to three years, or with both.`
  line
  line `97 Any person employed on inland vessel for`
  line `neglect or refusal to join or desertion of vessel`
  line `in violation of his obligation as provided`
  line `under section 97.`
  line `Forfeiture of a sum not exceeding two`
  line `days' pay, and in addition for every`
  line `twenty-four hours of absence, either a`
  line `sum not exceeding six days' pay or any`
  line `expenses properly incurred in hiring a`
  line `substitute, from his wages and also to`
  line `imprisonment which may extend to two`
  line months.
  line
  line `102 Any person found guilty of causing`
  line `obstruction or has acted in contravention of`
  line `section 102.`
  line `Fine which may extend to fifty thousand`
  line `rupees or imprisonment which may`
  line `extend to three years, or with both.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person who acts in contravention of the provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder,`
  line `but for which an offence is not specifically provided in this Act, shall be punishable with fine not`
  line `exceeding three lakh rupees or with imprisonment up to a term which may extend to three years, or with`
  line both.
  line
  line `(4) Where the owner or master of any mechanically propelled inland vessel is convicted of an offence`
  line `under this Act or any rule made thereunder, committed on board, or in relation to that mechanically`
  line `propelled vessel, and is sentenced to pay a fine, the Magistrate who passes the sentence may direct the`
  line `amount of the fine to be levied by distress and sale of the mechanically propelled vessel, or its`
  line `appurtenance so much thereof as is necessary.`
  line
  line `(5) Where an inland vessel has been used in contravention of the provisions of this Act or the rules`
  line `made thereunder, the details of the offence, the offender and the vessel shall be recorded in such form and`
  line `manner, as may be specified by the Central Government by notification.`
  line
  line `(6) The State Government shall appoint courts not inferior to that of a Magistrate of the first class, for`
  line `the purpose of conducting trial of any person who is charged of any offence as provided under this Act or`
  line `the rules made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (64048)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 88
  title `Offences by company, limited liability partnership firm or any such arrangement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64048&sectionno=88&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a company or a limited liability partnership firm`
  line `or any such arrangement, every person who, at the time the offence was committed was in-charge of, and`
  line `was responsible to the company or the limited liability partnership firm or any such arrangement, for the`
  line `conduct of the business, and the company or the limited liability partnership firm or any such`
  line `arrangement, shall be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and`
  line `punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he exercised all`
  line `due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company or a limited liability partnership firm or any such arrangement and it is proved`
  line `that the offence has been committed with the consent or connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or partner or other officer of the company or the limited`
  line `liability partnership firm or any such arrangement, as the case may be, such director, manager, secretary`
  line `or partner or other officer, as the case may be; shall also be deemed to be guilty of that offence and shall`
  line `be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (64049)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 89
  title `Fees, additional fee, payment and collection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64049&sectionno=89&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `(1) Unless otherwise specified, the State`
  line `Government shall collect, the fees and additional fees for the services provided under this Act and any`
  line `other charges or payment made to it against payments towards penalties, at such rates and intervals, as`
  line `may be prescribed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government shall appoint or authorise such officers, or constitute such offices within its`
  line `jurisdictions, by notification, to act as single point collection offices within the districts or ports,`
  line `considering proximity and convenience of remittance.`
  line
  line `(3) The procedures, forms and format of receipts, maintenance of accounts and any other matter that`
  line `is necessary for the purpose of the remittance, collection, accounts and accountability of collected fees,`
  line `additional fees, charges or payment against penalties of pecuniary nature shall be such as may be`
  line `prescribed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(4) The owner, operators or their representatives, as the case may be, shall remit the fees or additional`
  line `fees in such manner and at such rates as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(5) All fees payable under this Act may be recovered as fine under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (64050)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 90
  title `Cognizance of offence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64050&sectionno=90&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line `No court shall take cognizance of any offence under this Act, except`
  line `on a complaint in writing made by the Central Government or any officer authorised by the State`
  line `Government, as the case may be, for this purpose.`
obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_91:
  sectionId (64051)
  sectionNo (91)
  orderNo 91
  title `Local self-governance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_91_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64051&sectionno=91&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_91_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may authorise any of its department (herein`
  line `in this Chapter referred to as the authorised department) to administer and implement the provisions of`
  line `this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) The office of the authorised department shall be located at such places which are accessible to`
  line `owners, operators of non-mechanically propelled inland vessel and service users of such vessels.`
  line
  line `(3) The offices of the authorised department shall in the order of hierarchy of power, be at district,`
  line `taluk and panchayat or village level, or any other hierarchy as may be prescribed by the State`
  line `Government, and shall exercise the powers and functions as may be prescribed by that Government,`
  line `which shall include the powers and functions to—`
  line
  line `(a) enrol the non-mechanically propelled inland vessel under this Chapter;`
  line
  line `(b) collate data with regard to the non-mechanically propelled inland vessel enrolled under this`
  line `Act and report it to the higher authority in the hierarchy of power;`
  line
  line `(c) administer the welfare fund constituted under this Chapter in accordance with such authority`
  line `and obligation;`
  line
  line `(d) advise and conduct awareness programmes for assisting the owners, operators or service users`
  line `of non-mechanically propelled inland vessel enrolled under this Act; and`
  line
  line `(e) perform such other functions as may be assigned under this Act or the rules made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_92:
  sectionId (64052)
  sectionNo (92)
  orderNo 92
  title `Obligation to enroll.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_92_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64052&sectionno=92&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_92_content:
  string
  line `(1) The owner or operator may enrol, by submitting the details of the`
  line `ownership of non-mechanically propelled inland vessel, undertaking that the vessel is put into motion by`
  line `solely employing human labour and such other details as may be prescribed by the State Government, at`
  line `the office of the authorised department, which is located nearest to the place of residence of the owner or`
  line `area of plying of the non-mechanically propelled inland vessel, in such form and manner as may be`
  line `prescribed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The form prescribed by the State Government under sub-section (1) shall be published in the`
  line `respective vernacular language, apart from Hindi or English, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of identification and categorisation of non-mechanically propelled inland vessels,`
  line `to be enrolled in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (1), the State Government shall publish`
  line `such criteria for categorisation which may include the size, purpose of employment, age, construction,`
  line `design or such other criteria of the vessels.`
  line
  line `(4) The enrolment of non-mechanically propelled inland vessels shall be a prerequisite for such`
  line `vessels to be entitled for the benefits and preferential treatment accorded under this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(5) The details of the enrolled vessels shall be recorded in the registry of enrolment and be reported`
  line `by the offices of lowest order in the hierarchy of power to the highest hierarchy and the collated list of`
  line `enrolled vessels shall be maintained by the office of District Magistrate or such officer appointed or`
  line `authorised under this Chapter, for the said purpose.`
  line
  line `(6) The State Government shall maintain a central data base to record the details of the nonmechanically propelled inland vessel enrolled within the respective jurisdiction, in such form and manner as may be prescribed by it.`
  line
  line `(7) The lowest ranking officer of the office of the authorised department shall report of any change to`
  line `the registry of enrolment maintained by him and bring to the notice of the authority higher in the`
  line `hierarchical order, and the changes shall be brought out accordingly, in every such register maintained by`
  line `the respective authorities including the central data base maintained by the Principal Secretary or`
  line `Secretary of the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_93:
  sectionId (64053)
  sectionNo (93)
  orderNo 93
  title `Certificate of enrolment and marking of vessel.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_93_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64053&sectionno=93&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_93_content:
  string
  line `(1) The officer of the authorised department`
  line `appointed or authorised to maintain the registry under this Chapter, shall issue a certificate of enrolment`
  line `to the non-mechanically propelled inland vessels that have enrolled in the registry of enrolment.`
  line
  line `(2) The certificate of enrolment shall be issued, in such form and manner as may be prescribed by the`
  line `respective State Government, and details to be specified in such certificate shall include---`
  line
  line `(a) name, permanent address as given in the Unique Identification Document issued by Unique`
  line `Identification Authority of India, electoral identification document or such other document of the`
  line `owner, as may be prescribed by the State Government;`
  line
  line `(b) details such as year of construction, laying of keel or such other information;`
  line
  line `(c) details of design, if identified or categorised under this Chapter;`
  line
  line `(d) details of officer issuing or granting the certificate; and`
  line
  line `(e) number given to the vessels enrolled by the issuing authority.`
  line
  line `(3) The authorised department in every State shall issue a number to the non-mechanically propelled`
  line `inland vessel enrolled within the respective jurisdiction, which shall be unique for the purpose of`
  line `identification of enrolment with the authorised department of the respective State.`
  line
  line `(4) The number so issued under sub-section (3) shall be exhibited on a conspicuous part of the nonmechanically propelled inland vessel in such form and manner as may be prescribed by the respective`
  line `State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_94:
  sectionId (64054)
  sectionNo (94)
  orderNo 94
  title `Standards of construction and safety.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_94_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64054&sectionno=94&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_94_content:
  string
  line `(1) The basic minimum standards that may be`
  line `reasonably observed during the construction of any non-mechanically propelled inland vessel, shall be`
  line `such as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the State Government shall specify, the`
  line `standards of construction, which any class or category of non-mechanically propelled inland vessel shall`
  line `comply with, in such manner as may be prescribed by it:`
  line
  line `Provided that the standards prescribed by the State Government shall be in harmony with the`
  line `traditional knowledge and practices passed on as customary or ancestral means that are applied by skilled`
  line `and talented persons involved in the designing and construction of non-mechanically propelled inland`
  line vessel.
  line
  line `(3) The State Government may specify the minimum safety gears and equipment by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette with which the non-mechanically propelled inland vessel shall be equipped with for`
  line `the purpose of ensuring safety of such vessels.`
  line
  line `(4) The State Government may provide for standards of overhauling, modifying, altering or refitting`
  line `the non-mechanically propelled inland vessel for the purpose of ensuring safe navigation.`
  line
  line `(5) The non-mechanically propelled inland vessels enrolled under this Act, shall comply with the`
  line `safety standards as stipulated under this Chapter or the rules made in this regard.`
  line
  line `(6) For the purposes of ensuring safe navigation of non-mechanically propelled inland vessels, the`
  line `State Government may, by notification, specify the routes, areas or stretch of inland waters that are`
  line `prohibited from being used or subject to such terms and conditions, for the navigation of nonmechanically propelled inland vessel.`
obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_95:
  sectionId (64078)
  sectionNo (95)
  orderNo 95
  title `Power of State Government to make rules to regulate non-mechanically propelled inland vessels.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_95_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64078&sectionno=95&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_95_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by rules made in this behalf, specify the measures to regulate`
  line `non-mechanically propelled inland vessels.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of sub-section (1), the State Government may make rules for the following,`
  line `namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) for prevention and minimising pollution caused by the non-mechanically propelled inland`
  line vessels;
  line
  line `(b) for removal of obstructions to safe navigation;`
  line
  line `(c) measures that may be adopted to avert accidents and casualty; and`
  line
  line `(d) any other measure which the State Government may deem fit in implementing the provisions`
  line `of this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_96:
  sectionId (64056)
  sectionNo (96)
  orderNo 96
  title `Constitution of welfare fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_96_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64056&sectionno=96&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_96_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every State Government shall, by notification, constitute a`
  line `welfare fund at district level, for allocation of such fund to assist the non-mechanically propelled inland`
  line `vessels enrolled under this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) Any officer appointed or authorised under this Chapter to be in-charge of the fund for the nonmechanically propelled inland vessel shall, with the previous approval in writing of the respective State`
  line `Government or such other authority appointed for the said purpose, utilise the fund to—`
  line
  line `(a) create awareness and conduct knowledge dissemination sessions for educating the owner,`
  line `operator and service user on improvements required for safe navigation;`
  line
  line `(b) provide equipment and devices of safety and navigation at a subsidised rate;`
  line
  line `(c) provide support or relief during casualties, accidents or such emergencies; and`
  line
  line `(d) for such other purposes as it may deem fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_97:
  sectionId (64057)
  sectionNo (97)
  orderNo 97
  title `Desertion and absence without leave.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_97_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64057&sectionno=97&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_97_content:
  string
  line `No person employed or engaged in any capacity on`
  line `board a mechanically propelled vessel shall—`
  line
  line `(a) neglect or refuse, without reasonable cause, to join his mechanically propelled vessel or to`
  line `proceed on any voyage in his vessel;`
  line
  line `(b) cause to be absent from his vessel or from his duty at any time without leave and without`
  line `sufficient cause;`
  line
  line `(c) desert from his mechanically propelled vessel;`
  line
  line `(d) fail to act or behave with discipline befitting his duty and mandate.`
obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_98:
  sectionId (64058)
  sectionNo (98)
  orderNo 98
  title `General powers of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_98_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64058&sectionno=98&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_98_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may`
  line `make rules for—`
  line
  line `(a) implementation of standards for the use of special category of vessels within inland`
  line waterways;
  line
  line `(b) providing the requirements and standards of—`
  line
  line `(i) river information services;`
  line
  line `(ii) vessel traffic and transport management, safety and information services;`
  line
  line `(iii) vessel tracing and tracking information;`
  line
  line `(iv) to tackle calamities and furtherance of emergency preparedness;`
  line
  line `(v) to quarantine the vessels and to adopt such other measures to effectively control any`
  line `epidemic or disease of contagious nature;`
  line
  line `(c) enforcing standards to avoid and tackle pollution arising in inland waterways;`
  line
  line `(d) exemption, inclusion or extension of the application of any or all the provisions of this Act to`
  line `any vessel registered, recognised or identified and intended to ply, or plying in the inland waters;`
  line
  line `(e) any other matter as it may deem fit and necessary in the proper implementation of this Act for`
  line `the purposes of ensuring safe navigation, safety of life and prevention of pollution caused by inland`
  line vessel.
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of administration of the notifications mentioned in sub-section (1), the Central Government or the State Government, as the case may be, shall authorise or appoint officers by`
  line notification.
obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_99:
  sectionId (64059)
  sectionNo (99)
  orderNo 99
  title `Emergency preparedness.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_99_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64059&sectionno=99&orderno=99&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_99_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every State Government may, appoint or authorise the advisory`
  line `committee or officers, by notification, to take adequate measures, as may be prescribed by the State`
  line `Government, to minimise or counter emergency.`
  line
  line `(2) The owner, operator, master, crew or any other person connected with inland vessel plying in`
  line `inland waters shall upon finding or apprehending a situation of crisis, which could adversely affect or is`
  line `adversely affecting the safety of navigation, safety of human life or preservation of inland waters, inform`
  line `or report the advisory committee or such other officers, appointed under sub-section (1) having respective`
  line `jurisdiction or jurisdictions over such crisis that is found or is anticipated to affect adversely.`
  line
  line `(3) The advisory committee or officers, who are appointed or authorised under sub-section (1), on`
  line `receipt of information under sub-section (2), or as directed by the Central Government or the State Government or on their own initiative, may record the crisis as emergency and, shall adopt such measures`
  line `as prescribed under sub-section (1), and such other measures which are feasible and in best of the`
  line `judgment necessary to minimise or counter such emergency.`
  line
  line `(4) The advisory committee or officers, appointed or authorised under sub-section (1) may request the`
  line `navy, coast guard, any other emergency force, or any inland vessel available for such assistance as`
  line necessary.
  line
  line `(5) No mechanically propelled inland vessel directed or acting voluntarily in rendering assistance as`
  line `mentioned in sub-section (4) shall be bound by the provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(6) Any mechanically propelled inland vessel acting voluntarily, for the purpose of saving life or`
  line `vessel or providing basic amenities, shall report to the advisory committee or officers appointed or`
  line `authorised under sub-section (1) regarding the presence and reasons for the acts in writing, at the earliest`
  line possible.
  line
  line `(7) The advisory committee or officers appointed or authorised under sub-section (1) shall disburse`
  line `all basic amenities necessary and essential as it may deem fit, to the persons or vessels affected by such`
  line emergency.
  line
  line `(8) The advisory committee or officers appointed or authorised under sub-section (1) shall report to`
  line `the Central Government or the State Government, the complete description of the events, consequences`
  line `and such measures adopted under sub-section (3) and the effectiveness of such measures in countering the`
  line emergency.
obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_100:
  sectionId (64060)
  sectionNo (100)
  orderNo 100
  title `Removal of lawful obstruction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_100_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64060&sectionno=100&orderno=100&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_100_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any obstruction or impediment to the navigation of any`
  line `inland water has been lawfully made or has become lawful by reason of the long continuance of such`
  line `obstruction or impediment or otherwise, the authorised officer shall report the same for the information of`
  line `the State Government and shall, with the sanction of the State Government, cause the same to be removed`
  line `or altered, making reasonable compensation to the person suffering damage by such removal or alteration.`
  line
  line `(2) Any dispute arising out of or concerning such compensation shall be determined according to the`
  line `provisions of the Right to Fair Compensation and Transparency in Land Acquisition, Rehabilitation and`
  line `Resettlement Act, 2013 (30 of 2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_101:
  sectionId (64061)
  sectionNo (101)
  orderNo 101
  title `Validity of certificates issued under laws other than this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_101_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64061&sectionno=101&orderno=101&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_101_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every certificate issued in`
  line `respect of any person or vessel, under any other enactment in force in India, by the Central Government,`
  line `shall be valid and effective as a certificate issued under this Act and the relevant provisions of this Act`
  line `shall apply in relation to such persons or vessel as they apply to, any person who has been issued with a`
  line `certificate under Chapter VI or any mechanically propelled inland vessel registered, recognised or`
  line `identified under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained herein, the State Government may impose additional`
  line `conditions and requirements for the purpose of recognition of certificates as provided under`
  line `sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_102:
  sectionId (64062)
  sectionNo (102)
  orderNo 102
  title `Obstruction to officer appointed or authorised.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_102_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64062&sectionno=102&orderno=102&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_102_content:
  string
  line `No person shall wilfully cause obstruction`
  line `or attempt to obstruct any authority or officer appointed under this Act in exercise of the respective`
  line `functions and powers conferred upon such authority or officer, or in the discharge of any duty imposed by`
  line `or under this Act; by abstinence, failure to facilitate inspection, or restraining or physically objecting the`
  line `entry or movement or non-production of books or records as and when demanded by such authority or`
  line `authorised officers.`
obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_103:
  sectionId (64063)
  sectionNo (103)
  orderNo 103
  title `Place of trial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_103_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64063&sectionno=103&orderno=103&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_103_content:
  string
  line `Whoever contravenes any of the provisions of this Act or the rules made`
  line `thereunder, shall be triable for the offence in any place where he may be found or at the place of`
  line `occurrence or at the place in the State where the offence has been committed or a place which the Central`
  line `Government or the State Government, as the case may be, by notification, specify in this behalf, or any`
  line `other place in which he might be tried under any other enactment for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_104:
  sectionId (64064)
  sectionNo (104)
  orderNo 104
  title `Composition of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_104_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64064&sectionno=104&orderno=104&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_104_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), any offence punishable under this Act, not being an offence punishable with imprisonment only, or with imprisonment and also with fine, may, on an application of the accused`
  line `person, either before or after the institution of any prosecution, be compounded by competent authority or`
  line `in the event of the matter being referred to the court of competent jurisdiction, such offence may be`
  line `compounded by the competent authority with the permission of such court.`
  line
  line `(2) The competent authority referred to in sub-section (1) shall exercise the powers to compound an`
  line `offence, subject to the direction, control and supervision of the appropriate Government.`
  line
  line `(3) Every application for the compounding of an offence shall be made in such manner as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(4) Where any offence is compounded before the institution of any prosecution, no prosecution shall`
  line `be instituted in relation to such offence, against the offender in relation to whom the offence is so`
  line compounded.
  line
  line `(5) Where the composition of any offence is made after the institution of any prosecution, such`
  line `composition shall be brought by the competent authority referred to in sub-section (1) in writing, to the`
  line `notice of the court in which the prosecution is pending and on such notice of the composition of the`
  line `offence being given, the person against whom the offence is so compounded shall be discharged.`
  line
  line `(6) Any person who fails to comply with an order made by the competent authority referred to in subsection (1), shall be liable to pay a sum equivalent to twenty per cent. of the maximum fine provided for the offence, in addition to such fine.`
  line
  line `(7) No offence punishable under the provisions of this Act shall be compounded except under and in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_105:
  sectionId (64065)
  sectionNo (105)
  orderNo 105
  title Appeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_105_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64065&sectionno=105&orderno=105&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_105_content:
  string
  line `(1) Unless otherwise provided in this Act, any person aggrieved by an order made by`
  line `the officers or authorities under this Act, may appeal to the State Government against refusal, suspension,`
  line `cancellation, detention, removal or such other order, issued under this Act, within thirty days from the`
  line `date of receipt of such order.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government shall cause notice of every such appeal to be given to concerned officers or`
  line `authorities whose order is made the subject matter of the appeal, and after giving an opportunity to the`
  line `appellant; shall pass appropriate order by recording reasons thereof, which shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_106:
  sectionId (64066)
  sectionNo (106)
  orderNo 106
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_106_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64066&sectionno=106&orderno=106&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_106_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of effective`
  line `implementation of the provisions of this Act, the Central Government shall, subject to the condition of`
  line `previous publication, make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the centralised record to be maintained in e-portal, for recording the data and details of vessel,`
  line `vessel registration, crew, manning, certificates issued, reception facilities and such other data to be`
  line `recorded under clause (f) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) the requirements for compliance to be specified in a cover note for the purpose of issuance of certificate of insurance under clause (g) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(c) the procedure to be laid down and rates to be specified so as to calculate the rate of extent of`
  line `liability within which the owner or such other persons entitled under this Act, may limit the liability`
  line `or be permitted to limit or cap the liability arising out of claims under clause (t) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(d) the standard and number of persons required for safe manning and navigation of vessels under`
  line `clause (z) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(e) the classification, criteria for such classification and standards of design, construction, fitness`
  line `and crew accommodation to classify or categorise any mechanically propelled inland vessel under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(f) the manner of carrying out construction and any alteration or modification of mechanically`
  line `propelled inland vessels with the prior approval of design from the designated authority under`
  line `section 8;`
  line
  line `(g) the standards for type and periodicity of surveys for all mechanically propelled inland vessels,`
  line `which are newly constructed and already in service under sub-section (1) and the form and content of`
  line `request for survey to be submitted by the applicant under sub-section (2) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(h) the minimum criteria and qualifications for the appointment of surveyors, which the State`
  line `Governments shall adopt in the appointment of surveyors under section 10;`
  line
  line `(i) the form of application for conducting survey to be submitted by owners, masters or`
  line `construction yard under sub-section (1) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(j) the form and contents of the declaration of survey of a mechanically propelled inland vessel`
  line `and the time period for which such certificate shall be valid, under sub-section (1) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(k) the form of the certificate of survey including any particulars or terms and conditions under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(l) the form of provisional certificate of survey and the period of validity provided under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(m) the terms and conditions to be complied with for permitting any mechanically propelled`
  line `vessels registered under such laws of countries other than India; which shall only be permitted to ply`
  line `within the inland waters under clause (c) of sub-section (2) of section 18;`
  line
  line `(n) the form, contents or particulars of the book of registry as provided under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 21;`
  line
  line `(o) the form and manner for maintenance of central data base for inland vessels by the officers`
  line `appointed by the Central Government under section 22;`
  line
  line `(p) the functions to be performed by the officers appointed by the Central Government under`
  line `section 22;`
  line
  line `(q) the form and manner of making application for registration of a mechanically propelled inland`
  line `vessel and the particulars along with which such application is to be made under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 23;`
  line
  line `(r) the list of documents to be submitted or adduced by the applicants for registration under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 23;`
  line
  line `(s) the form and content of certificate of registration under sub-section (2) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(t) the form of application, fee and the manner of issuance of provisional certificate of registration under sub-section (2) of section 27;`
  line
  line `(u) the procedures to be complied with by the owner of any mechanically propelled inland vessel`
  line `who ceases to be the owner or applies for the requirement of transfer of registry or any such`
  line `circumstances leading to change of the registered address under sub-section (2) of section 29;`
  line
  line `(v) the procedures for validating the transfer of mechanically propelled inland vessel from India`
  line `to outside India under section 30;`
  line
  line `(w) the time within which the owner of the mechanically propelled inland vessel shall report to`
  line `the Registrar of Inland Vessels of the place where such vessel is registered, if that vessel is declared`
  line `missing, destroyed, lost, abandoned or has been rendered permanently unfit for service or destined for`
  line `scrapping or dismantling or sold abroad;`
  line
  line `(x) the form of instrument creating the security for a mortgage for a loan or other valuable`
  line `consideration under sub-section (1) of section 33;`
  line
  line `(y) the manner and conditions governing mortgage and its procedures under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 33;`
  line
  line `(z) the standards for qualification, training, training institute, examination and grant of`
  line `competency certificates under sub-section (1) of section 34;`
  line
  line `(za) the minimum manning scale applicable to different class or category of mechanically`
  line `propelled inland vessels, categorised under this Act or such other laws for the time being in force in`
  line `India, under section 35;`
  line
  line `(zb) the criteria and qualifications for appointment of examiners under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 36;`
  line
  line `(zc) the form, contents and particulars of certificate of competency specified under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 37;`
  line
  line `(zd) the period of validity of certificate of service issued under sub-section (1) of section 38;`
  line
  line `(ze) the form of certificate of service and the conditions subject to which such certificate is issued`
  line `under sub-section (4) of section 38;`
  line
  line `(zf) the conditions subject to which the certificate of competency shall be valid throughout India`
  line `under section 39;`
  line
  line `(zg) the intervals and manner in which the State Government shall report and update the Central`
  line `Government with the information on data and details of certificates issued, granted, cancelled or`
  line `suspended or such other remarks, made by the respective authority under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 41;`
  line
  line `(zh) the criteria and standards to identify any class or category of mechanically propelled inland`
  line `vessels as special category vessels based on their design, construction, use, purpose, area of plying,`
  line `source of energy or fuelling or any other criteria under sub-section (1) of section 42;`
  line
  line `(zi) the requirements of construction, design, survey, registration, manning, qualification,`
  line `competency, or the requirements in addition to those contained elsewhere in this Act under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 42;`
  line
  line `(zj) the specifications and requirements of signals and equipment based on classification and`
  line `categorisation of mechanically propelled vessels, to be complied with by such vessels under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 47;`
  line
  line `(zk) the fog and distress signals to be carried and used, the steering and sailing rules to be`
  line `complied with and the different protocols for exhibition and display of different standards of lights,`
  line `shapes and signals, by any mechanically propelled vessel plying in inland waters under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 47;`
  line
  line `(zl) the class or category of mechanically propelled inland vessels to be equipped with navigation`
  line `aids, life saving appliances, fire detection and extinguishing appliances and communication`
  line `appliances under sub-section (1) of section 51;`
  line
  line `(zm) the standards to be followed by the owner or master of any mechanically propelled inland`
  line `vessel and the manner for discharge or dispose of sewage and garbage under sub-section (2) of section 52;`
  line
  line `(zn) the standards of construction and equipment of the mechanically propelled inland vessels to`
  line `ensure compliance with the requirements of the provisions of Chapter IX under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 53;`
  line
  line `(zo) the form, validity and content of prevention of pollution certificate under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 53;`
  line
  line `(zp) the conditions for construction, use and maintenance of reception facilities for the`
  line `containment of pollution and removal of pollutants arising from spillage or discharge arising from`
  line `mechanically propelled inland vessels at all cargo terminals or passenger terminals under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 54;`
  line
  line `(zq) the purposes for Chapter X as specified in clauses (a) to (g) of section 59;`
  line
  line `(zr) the limits of liability and the criteria in determining compensation for any claim specified in`
  line `sub-section (5) of section 64;`
  line
  line `(zs) the form, content, and the conditions subject to which a certificate of insurance is issued by`
  line `the insurer to the insured under clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 68;`
  line
  line `(zt) the terms and conditions to be incorporated in the contract of insurance entered between`
  line `insurer and insured to cover the risks, as provided in section 66, under sub-section (2) of section 68;`
  line
  line `(zu) the terms, conditions and procedures to be complied with by insurers and insured including`
  line `those specified in clauses (a) to (h) therein, under section 73;`
  line
  line `(zv) minimum standards, terms and conditions to protect the interests and to ensure safety of`
  line `service providers and service users under section 80;`
  line
  line `(zw) the conditions for carrying the list of dangerous goods under section 81;`
  line
  line `(zx) the terms and conditions subject to which permission of the Central Government is granted`
  line `for use or employment of a vessel, registered in any country other than India, for the purposes of,`
  line `carriage of goods, transportation of passengers, storage units, accommodation, floating units or for`
  line `such other purposes within the inland waters under sub-section (1) of section 82;`
  line
  line `(zy) the fees for grant of a certificate or licence under this Act similar to any certificate granted by`
  line `any other foreign country in accordance with the provisions of any law for the time being in force in`
  line `that country under sub-section (2) of section 82;`
  line
  line `(zz) the period and extent of validity of certificate granted under sub-section (2) of section 82, as`
  line `specified in sub-section (3) of the said section;`
  line
  line `(zza) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed under the provisions of this`
  line `Act for the purpose of implementation and administration of such provisions.`
obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_107:
  sectionId (64067)
  sectionNo (107)
  orderNo 107
  title `Power of State Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_107_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64067&sectionno=107&orderno=107&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_107_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, after previous`
  line `publication, make rules for the provisions specified to be administered by it under this Act or as delegated`
  line `to it by the Central Government for the purposes of effective implementation of the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the requirements for the appointment of qualified persons as pilots under clause (zk) of`
  line `section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) the fee for issuance of certificate of survey under sub-section (2) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner and conditions subject to which any mechanically propelled inland vessel, which`
  line `has been issued with a provisional certificate of survey or endorsement may proceed on voyage or use`
  line `in service, temporarily, pending the issue of certificate of survey under sub-section (2) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(d) the manner of issue the notice of suspension of certificate of survey to the owner, operator,`
  line `master, or construction yard under sub-section (2) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(e) the functions to be performed by the Registrar of Inland Vessels in respect to the port or place`
  line `of registry for which he is appointed under sub-section (2) of section 20;`
  line
  line `(f) the manner and period in which the Registrar of Inland Vessels shall report the details of the`
  line `book of registry or entries made therein, to the State Government at regular intervals, under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 21;`
  line
  line `(g) the fee for granting the certificate of registration to the applicant under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 24;`
  line
  line `(h) other particulars to be contained in the certificate of registration under clause (e) of`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(i) the conspicuous part of the vessel where the owner shall display the official number under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(j) the form and manner in which the registered owner shall apply for a duplicate certificate to the`
  line `Registrar of Inland Vessels under sub-section (1) of section 26;`
  line
  line `(k) the fees or additional fees for applying for a duplicate certificate to the Registrar of Inland`
  line `Vessels under sub-section (2) of section 26;`
  line
  line `(l) the form, manner and period within which the owner, operator or master of the mechanically`
  line `propelled inland vessel shall make an application, for entry of alterations or modifications made, in`
  line `the certificate of registration, under sub-section (1) of section 28;`
  line
  line `(m) the fee for applying to the Registrar of Inland Vessels for registration of alterations under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 28;`
  line
  line `(n) the conditions to be complied with and the period for such compliance to be stated in the`
  line `notice of suspension issued by the Registrar of Inland Vessels under sub-section (4) of section 31;`
  line
  line `(o) the form and manner for maintenance of registers to record, the details and data of the`
  line `certificate, and the certificates specified therein, under sub-section (1) of section 41;`
  line
  line `(p) the form of application, form of certificate of fitness and such other conditions including`
  line `validity, subject to which and the manner of granting the certificate of fitness under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 43;`
  line
  line `(q) the safety features, gears and such other measures by which any mechanically propelled`
  line `inland vessel, identified as special category vessel, shall comply with and be equipped in accordance`
  line `with the categorisation of such vessel, under sub-section (1) of section 44;`
  line
  line `(r) the maximum carrying capacity of the vessel identified as special category vessel by`
  line `specifying the safety waterline or the limits of load water line to keep them afloat, or such other`
  line `criteria and conditions, for the safe voyage of such inland vessel under sub-section (2) of section 44;`
  line
  line `(s) the rates of charges to be received by the owner or operator of all cargo terminals or passenger`
  line `terminals, providing reception facilities shall receive charges under sub-section (3) of section 54;`
  line
  line `(t) the form of report of compliance to be submitted by the owner or operator of the passenger or`
  line `cargo terminal under sub-section (5) of section 54;`
  line
  line `(u) the manner in which the owner, operator or master of any mechanically propelled vessel used`
  line `or plying within inland waters, shall discharge the pollutants at the port reception facilities under`
  line `sub-section (6) of section 54;`
  line
  line `(v) the procedure for detaining any mechanically propelled inland vessel in connection with a`
  line `claim, or an offence under section 63;`
  line
  line `(w) the form and manner of giving information of any wreck, abandonment, damage, casualty,`
  line `accident, explosion or loss occurred to or on board such a vessel while in the inland waters, to the`
  line `officer in-charge of the nearest police station and to the designated authority appointed under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 74;`
  line
  line `(x) the powers of the District Magistrate and the procedures to be followed in holding inquiry`
  line `under sub-section (3) of section 75;`
  line
  line `(y) the qualifications, criteria and consideration, fees or charges for the assessors, who have`
  line `experience in the merchant service or in the navigation of the mechanically propelled inland vessels`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 76;`
  line
  line `(z) the procedures for detention, formality, fees and conditions, if not specified in this Act, to be`
  line `followed and observed by the concerned officer or authority or court, appointed or authorised or`
  line `constituted under this Act, for the purpose of detaining a vessel, under sub-section (4) of section 85;`
  line
  line `(za) the rates of fees and additional fees to be charged for the services provided under this Act,`
  line `and any other charges or payment made to it against penalties of pecuniary nature to be collected by`
  line `the State Government, and the intervals at which such fees, charges or penalties shall be collected,`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 89;`
  line
  line `(zb) the procedures, forms and format of receipts, maintenance of accounts and any other matter`
  line `that is necessary for the purpose of the remittance, collection, accounts and accountability of collected`
  line `fees, additional fees, charges or payment against penalties of pecuniary nature under sub-section (3)`
  line `of section 89;`
  line
  line `(zc) the manner and rates of fees or additional fees, the owner, operators or their representatives,`
  line `as the case may be, shall remit under sub-section (4) of section 89;`
  line
  line `(zd) the hierarchy of the offices of the authorised department and the powers and functions to be`
  line `exercised by such offices under sub-section (3) of section 91;`
  line
  line `(ze) the authority and obligation to administer the welfare fund constituted for the purposes of`
  line `Chapter XVII under clause (c) of sub-section (3) of section 91;`
  line
  line `(zf) such other details to be submitted by the owner or operator of non-mechanically propelled`
  line `inland vessel at the office of the authorised department and the form and manner of making such`
  line `submission, under sub-section (1) of section 92;`
  line
  line `(zg) the form and manner of central data base to record the details of non-mechanically propelled`
  line `inland vessels under sub-section (6) of section 92;`
  line
  line `(zh) the form and manner of issuance of certificate of enrolment and such other document`
  line `containing details of the owner, to be specified in the said certificate, under sub-section (2) of section`
  line 93;
  line
  line `(zi) the form and manner of exhibiting a number issued to a non-mechanically propelled inland`
  line `vessel under sub-section (4) of section 93;`
  line
  line `(zj) the basic minimum standards that may be reasonably observed during the construction of any`
  line `non-mechanically propelled inland vessel under sub-section (1) of section 94;`
  line
  line `(zk) the manner of complying with the standards of construction specified by the State`
  line `Government, by any class or category of non-mechanically propelled inland vessel under sub-section`
  line `(2) of section 94;`
  line
  line `(zl) the measures to regulate the non-mechanically propelled inland vessel under section 95;`
  line
  line `(zm) the measures to be taken by the advisory committee or officers authorised in this behalf to`
  line `minimise or counter emergency under sub-section (1) of section 99;`
  line
  line `(zn) for the purposes of implementation and administration of Chapter XVII of this Act,`
  line `pertaining to non-mechanically propelled inland vessels;`
  line
  line `(zo) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed under the provisions of`
  line `this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_108:
  sectionId (64068)
  sectionNo (108)
  orderNo 108
  title `Power of Central Government to give directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_108_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64068&sectionno=108&orderno=108&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_108_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, for`
  line `carrying into execution of this Act in the State, give directions to the State Government, and the State`
  line `Government shall abide by such directions.`
obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_109:
  sectionId (64069)
  sectionNo (109)
  orderNo 109
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_109_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64069&sectionno=109&orderno=109&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_109_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding`
  line `shall lie against any person or officer appointed or authorised under this Act, in respect of anything done`
  line `or intended to be done in good faith under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of claiming immunity under sub-section (1), the officers appointed or authorised`
  line `under this Act, shall perform and carry out the respective functions and responsibilities, with utmost care`
  line `and due diligence.`
obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_110:
  sectionId (64070)
  sectionNo (110)
  orderNo 110
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_110_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64070&sectionno=110&orderno=110&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_110_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as may appear to it to be necessary for removing the`
  line `difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made under this section after the expiry of a period of three`
  line `years, from the commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_111:
  sectionId (64071)
  sectionNo (111)
  orderNo 111
  title `Consistency with other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_111_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64071&sectionno=111&orderno=111&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_111_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of this Act shall be in addition to, and not be`
  line `construed in derogation of the provisions of any other law, and shall be construed as consistent with such`
  line `law, for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(2) In the event of any conflict between a provision of this Act and a provision of any other law for`
  line `the time being in force in the whole of India or restricted to the application within the territory of any`
  line `State, the provision of this Act shall prevail to the extent of such conflict.`
obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_112:
  sectionId (64072)
  sectionNo (112)
  orderNo 112
  title `Suspension or alteration of application and operation of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_112_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64072&sectionno=112&orderno=112&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_112_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government`
  line `may, by notification, declare that all or any of the provisions, under this Act or the rules made`
  line thereunder—
  line
  line `(a) other than that provided for safety, manning and prevention of pollution, shall not apply to`
  line `any specified class or category of the mechanically propelled inland vessels; or`
  line
  line `(b) shall apply to any specified class or category of the mechanically propelled inland vessels`
  line `with such modifications, as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, the Central Government may, by notification,`
  line `suspend or relax to a specified extent, either indefinitely or for such period as may be specified in that`
  line `notification, the operation of all or any of the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_113:
  sectionId (64073)
  sectionNo (113)
  orderNo 113
  title `Laying of rules and notifications.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_113_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64073&sectionno=113&orderno=113&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_113_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every rule made or notification issued under this Act,`
  line `by the Central Government shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made or issued, before each House`
  line `of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session`
  line `or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the`
  line `session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or`
  line `notification, or both Houses agree that the rule or notification should not be made, the rule or notification`
  line `shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however,`
  line `that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously`
  line `done under that rule or notification.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule made or notification issued under this Act by the State Government shall, as soon as`
  line `after it is made or issued, be laid before the State Legislature.`
obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_114:
  sectionId (64074)
  sectionNo (114)
  orderNo 114
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_114_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182&sectionId=64074&sectionno=114&orderno=114&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00002_202124_1645693186182
obj_root_law_sections_114_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Inland Vessels Act, 1917 (1 of 1917) is hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding the repeal of the enactment referred to in sub-section (1),—`
  line
  line `(a) any notification, rule, regulation, bye-law, order or exemption issued, made or granted under`
  line `the enactment hereby repealed shall, if it is not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, continue`
  line `to be in force unless and until revoked, and shall have effect as if it had been issued, made or granted`
  line `under the corresponding provision of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) any officer appointed and anybody elected or constituted under any enactment hereby`
  line `repealed shall continue and shall be deemed to have been appointed, elected or constituted unless`
  line `specifically removed or replaced by appointment of officer or offices, as the case may be, under this`
  line Act;
  line
  line `(c) any document referring to the enactment hereby repealed shall be constructed as referring to`
  line `this Act or to the corresponding provision of this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) any fine levied or penalty imposed under the enactment hereby repealed may be recovered as`
  line `if it had been levied under this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) any offence committed under the enactment hereby repealed may be prosecuted and punished`
  line `as if it had been committed under this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) sailing vessels or sailing boats registered under the enactment hereby repealed shall be deemed`
  line `to have been registered under the Act;`
  line
  line `(g) mortgages of any mechanically propelled inland vessels recorded in any register book`
  line `maintained at any port in India under the enactment hereby repealed shall be deemed to have been`
  line `recorded in the register book under the corresponding provision of this Act;`
  line
  line `(h) any licence, certificate of competency or service, certificate of survey, licenses or any other`
  line `certificate or document issued, made or granted under the enactment hereby repealed and in force at`
  line `the commencement of this Act shall be deemed to have been issued, made or granted under this Act`
  line `and shall, unless cancelled under this Act, continue in force until the date shown in the certificate or`
  line `document, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(3) The matters specifically provided in this section, shall not be held to prejudice or affect the`
  line `general application of section 6 of the General Clauses Act, 1897 (X of 1897).`
obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes:
  string
  line
